title: kim chee
directions: Slice nappa in 2-inch strips and onions in long thin strips. Place nappa and onions in a container with salt and press with a weight for 1 hour.
Turn over and press 1 hour longer. Rinse and squeeze out liquid.
Mix in remaining dry ingredients.
Place in jars and store in the shade for 1 day, then refrigerate.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
toss
together the apples, celery, walnuts and raisins.
In
a
small	bowl, gently stir in lemon juice, sour cream and yogurt, then fold the 2 mixtures together. Cover and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls, butter, sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
In a double boiler melt chocolate chips, Hershey bar and paraphane.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Set on cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken, pork or ribs
directions: Cook onions in oil.
Add other ingredients and cook 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Sauce may be frozen.

title: sour cream blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine milk, egg and sour cream; beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; add to milk mixture. Beat just until large lumps disappear. Stir in butter. Fold in blueberries.

title: deluxe carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, salad dressing, eggs and pineapple juice together. Then add carrots; mix well.
Add soda and baking powder to flour. Slowly add to creamed mix.
Add vanilla.
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch or regular cake pans).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and oleo together.
Add baking powder, salt, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: jet-age brownies
directions: Combine oil
and cocoa.
Add sugars.
Blend.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add vanilla, then flour.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares.

title: braised cabbage
directions: In skillet, heat butter until foamy. Add onions or chives and saute until tender. Add cabbage and carrots. Saute over high heat until tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Mix all other ingredients together and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.
May sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix well.
Chill in freezer for slushiness.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add molasses.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add alternately with applesauce to first mixture.
Add raisins; mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350°
for 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain on paper towels. Dip into lemon juice and dredge in mixture of flour, salt and paprika. Brown quickly in oil. Arrange in 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle grated lemon peel, brown sugar and onion over chicken pieces. Pour in broth; cover tightly and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cake is good warm from the oven, but improves with age.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shrimp dip #1
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise thoroughly.
Add other ingredients.
Add shrimp last.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, preferably overnight, before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: In a buttered pan, place alternate layers of potatoes and onions.
Rub pork chops with salt and pepper on both sides.
Lay them on top of the potatoes and onions.
Pour the cream of tomato soup over them.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in water; add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix with a spoon.
Roll out and cut.
Use only enough flour to handle well.
May be used at once but is better if made the day before. Not necessary to let rise.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 38.

title: florentine sausage stuffing
directions: Cook sausage in butter until browned, stirring frequently. Stir in onion, celery, carrot and garlic.
Continue to cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and cook with water for 7 minutes.
Add sugar and cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove from fire and add the jello and dissolve.
Add the cold water and cool.
Add the apples, celery and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla with electric mixer.
In second bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Alternate mixing dry ingredients and baby food into sugar mixture until well blended. Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.
Cool upright on rack for 10 minutes, invert for remaining cooling time.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Sift together sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg (can use pumpkin pie spice in place of cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg).
Mix with pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined large pie plate.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes, until pie is done.

title: louisiana yam and pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices. Blend sugar, egg, oleo and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and yams.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Using a wire whisk, mix all ingredients until shrimp are shredded.
Chill.
Serve with choice of crackers and potato chips.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat well.
Spread 1/2 mix in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: Cook ground chuck in a large ovenproof skillet with lid over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well and pat meat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet with a paper towel.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat and mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oleo until golden.
Stir in meat, flour and seasonings and cook for 5 minutes.
Add soups and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: escalloped potatoes southern style
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, 1/2 stick melted butter or oleo, sour cream, grated cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix; place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grate or chop thin all peppers and onions.
Combine and scald for 5 minutes in own broth.
Drain excess liquid.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes over medium-high heat, stirring often.
Can in hot jars with hot sealers and caps (180 degrees). Do not move for 12 hours.
Check for seal before storage.

title: nagwa's cake
directions: Get a wide pot.
Mix eggs, butter, orange juice, sugar and vanilla in a mixer.
Put on them baking powder and flour and mix together again.
Put in pot.
Put in oven.
Takes 1 hour for it to bake at 350°.

title: nannie's pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs together.
Add sugar, cinnamon, soda, flour and pumpkin and mix well.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Spread pumpkin mixture evenly on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert on powdered sugar towel.
Peel off wax paper and roll in towel. While roll is cooling, make filling.

title: cajun shrimp balls(2 dozen)
directions: In a medium saucepan melt butter.
Add parsley and scallions; cook 1 minute.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in shrimp.
Shape into balls using 1 tablespoon mixture per ball.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Boil soup bones for 1 hour.
Remove from pot.
Add vegetables. Cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Turn off heat.
Let sit 15 minutes.
This soup is even better the second day.
It may be canned or frozen.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 1 week.
Makes 6 quarts, but may easily be reduced.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chilies rellenos bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add the first 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Place half the chilies in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chilies atop.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and the dash of pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted just off the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Pass the taco sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 2 at a time.
Beat well. Add vanilla.
Fold in crushed wafers, nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for a long time. Bake at 300°.

title: fried chicken
directions: Place cut up and skinned chicken in cold water; salt and drop several ice cubes in water. Soak for 45 to 60 minutes. Rinse chicken; drain and salt to taste. Roll chicken in flour and fry in electric skillet in hot, melted Crisco on 300° until done; turn 2 to 3 times. Enjoy tender-moist golden fried chicken.

title: cherry "dump" cake
directions: Spray oblong cake pan with Pam.
Heat oven to 350°.
Dump pineapple, including juice, in cake pan.
On top of that, spoon cherry pie filling, then spread cake mix on top of cherries, crushing lumps, then gently pour on top of cake mix the melted butter/margarine.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm, with ice cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: baked fish
directions: Spray baking dish (9 x 13-inches) with nonstick cooking spray. Place fish in dish with skin side down.
In small saucepan, melt butter with other ingredients.
Spoon over top of fish.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic powder; drain. Combine with sour cream.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture.
Roll tortillas and place in baking pan that is lightly coated with enchilada sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cut spears in large pieces.
Mix other ingredients together; add broccoli.
Place in lightly buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix until thick.
Add bananas and flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amaretto mix
directions: Blend
together
the coffee creamer and almond extract. Combine with other ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Use 2 tablespoons per cup hot water.

title: basic meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape mixture by tablespoonfuls into 1 1/2-inch balls.
(For ease in shaping the meatballs, occasionally wet your hands with cold water.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: mounds
directions: Melt butter slowly and add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add coconut and pecans.
Chill until it can be easily handled.
Roll into balls.
Place in refrigerator or freezer until firm.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and dip each candy ball in chocolate, using toothpick. Remove candy from chocolate quickly and place on wax paper.
Use another toothpick to push ball from inserted toothpick.
If hole remains where toothpick was inserted, smooth with spoon and a small amount of coating.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meat, onion and bell pepper, then boil lasagne until soft.
Spread about 3/4 cup meat sauce on bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Layer with cheese, meat mixture and lasagne until gone.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice krispies puffs
directions: Grate cheese and combine with margarine.
Mix all, adding cereal last.
Roll in small balls (can freeze at this point or after baked).
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: cheese ravioli-asparagus pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
In a medium-size bowl lightly beat eggs with a fork.
Stir in undiluted soup and pepper until blended.
Cover bottom of prepared pie pan with a single layer of ravioli.
Spoon 1/3 of soup mixture over ravioli.
Top with 1/2 the zucchini, tomatoes, basil and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, then top with remaining 1/3 cup soup mixture.
Bake 45 minutes before cutting in wedges.
Serves 4.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Toss candied fruit with flour in bowl to coat. Add coconut, pecans, condensed milk and salt; mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 25 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute. Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix together sugar, cocoa, salt, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add butter.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: caesar salad(mexican)
directions: Rub the inside of the salad bowl with the garlic clove.
Tear the lettuce into bite size pieces; add to salad bowl.
Place egg in pan of boiling water.
Cook 1 minute.
Break egg onto lettuce and toss.
Add lemon juice.
Toss again.
Sprinkle salad with Parmesan and croutons.
Add Caesar Salad Dressing.
Toss and serve.
Serves 6.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix together and heat in crock-pot.
Do not let this boil. Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: natural punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water and add all the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together and freeze in 6 (4-cup) containers (1/2 gallon jugs).
When ready to serve, cut jug and put in punch bowl. Pour 1 (2-liter) bottle of ginger ale or Sprite per each 1/2 gallon bottle of punch.
Serve.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix next 2 ingredients and carefully put over top of the crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from heat and top with 5 or 6 Hershey bars.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well.
Add crushed pineapple (juice and all).
Add thawed strawberries (juice and all).
Stir well.
Add mashed bananas.
Pour into Jell-O mold and refrigerate.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix salmon, salt, pepper, eggs and flour in bowl.
Chop onions and add to bowl.
Mix all ingredients well; roll into patties.
Heat oil in skillet.
Place salmon patties in skillet.
Brown evenly on both sides.
Serves 5.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Combine oats and brown sugar in bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Press into greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top. Let stand until chocolate melts; spread evenly over top.
Cut into bars while warm.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Mix sugar, juice, and butter together in a pan on stove and bring to a boil. Peel apples and cut into 4 pieces. Roll apple pieces in crescent roll;
place in baking pan and pour apple juice mixture over crescent apples. Bake at 350° for 25 min.

title: walnut wafers
directions: Beat eggs. Add all other ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 325°. Ovens are different so just watch until done.

title: morning fruit salad
directions: Scoop out cantaloupe with a melon baller and place balls in bowl.
Pour any cantaloupe juice in bowl.
Peel kiwi and cut crosswise into thin slices, then quarter the slices.
Add to cantaloupe. Set aside 4 of the most attractive strawberries for garnish.
Hull and slice enough strawberries lengthwise to make 1 cup.
Place in bowl.
Add raspberries. Sprinkle fruit salad with chopped mint leaves and drizzle with orange juice. Toss gently. Refrigerate, covered, for 1/2 hour and garnish.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place vegetables in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add soup, milk, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Mix. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until top browns.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core and parboil cabbage, head down, for 10 to 15 minutes, covered in 2 cups salted water.
Remove and cool; separate leaves. Mix remaining ingredients together until well blended.
On each cabbage leaf, place one tablespoon meat filling.
Roll loosely, folding in sides as you roll.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch baking pan or casserole dish with Pam.
Place slice of Jack cheese in each chile.
Place one layer of chiles in dish, sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and repeat layers.

title: make your own corn bread mix
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in cool, dry place.
Makes 9 1/2 cups mix.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: In small saucepan, place flour and enough milk to make paste. Slowly add rest of milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook on low fire, stirring constantly until thickens.
Place in refrigerator until cold.
Place in bowl the oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add flavoring and cold flour mixture.
Beat until fluffy. The more you beat it the better.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
(It should be real smooth and creamy.) Add eggs, one
at a time and blend each one separately. Add flour
and
blend.
Add
7-Up.	Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour Bundt
cake pan, bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar.
To mix, place 2 rounded teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water and pour over other ingredients.
Mix together and pat out to roll size.
Let rise in pan for 30 minutes.

title: recipe for a contented family
directions: Mix love and loyalty thoroughly with faith.
Blend in tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Add friendship and hope. Bake with sunshine for a lifetime.
Sprinkle with laughter and serve daily.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Eat with crackers or chips.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit, reserving pineapple juice. Combine juice, pudding mix and Tang.
Stir well.
Combine fruit and dressing; toss gently.
Chill.

title: fettucini with salami, mushrooms and cheese
directions: Rinse chicken under cool water; pat dry.
Place in a rectangular glass baking dish.
In a 1-cup glass measure, mix together juices, onion, marjoram, thyme, parsley, pepper and mint flakes.
Pour over chicken parts and turn to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours, turning several times to coat with marinade.

title: mexican brown sugar candy
directions: Stir together the sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave mixture on High for 5 minutes.
Add the margarine, peanuts and vanilla to mixture, stirring together.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add the baking soda; stir quickly.
Spread mixture on foil lined flat round pan; flatten mixture with hand to desired thickness.
After cooling, break into bite size pieces and enjoy!

title: dinner cut casserole
directions: Dip Dinner cuts in breading meal and egg; brown in large skillet.
Remove browned cuts and use same skillet for making the sauce.
Add mushrooms to oil in skillet and brown.
Combine sour cream and 2/3 cup liquid from Dinner cuts; add to mushrooms. Blend in garlic powder, broth and Veges.
Simmer for 5 minutes. In a large casserole dish, alternate layers of cuts, sauce and cheese.
Top with additional grated cheese.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: donnie's chili
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Combine everything in large pot. Cook for 45 minutes on high.
Stir frequently.
Reduce heat to low and continue to cook for 1 1/4 hours more.
Stir frequently.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Combine pineapple juice, coconut cream and a couple of handfuls of ice in a blender and process until thick and creamy.

title: tuna salad on a shoestring
directions: In large bowl, separate tuna into chunks.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Toss well.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, fold in potatoes.

title: marinated garden vegetable salad
directions: Combine salt, white vinegar, tarragon vinegar, salad oil, sugar and cold water and stir and dissolve before doing the following:

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Blend together on low speed with a mixer. Store in jars in refrigerator. Spoon over cream cheese. Serve with crackers. Also good over chicken or on English muffins. Keeps a long time!

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger until redness is gone.
Drain grease.
Put onion, garlic, oregano, cumin, salt, chili powder and juice in blender.
Blend until onion and garlic are smooth.
Pour into hamburger and beans.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes to an hour.

title: easy corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in buttermilk, oil and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into hot greased pan (9-inch or larger).
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mother martha's ten-inch cream cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese and butter get soft.
Then add sour cream. Mix all ingredients with electric hand mixer.
Add cornstarch, mix. Add vanilla, mix.
Add lemon juice, mix.
Add sugar, mix.
Beat all ingredients together and mix well.
Then add eggs one at a time, mix well.
Place ingredients into a 10 inch spring form pan.
Place pan into a roasting pan half filled with hot water.
Place in preheated oven at 375 for 1 hour.
Take from oven and place on rack and let cool.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Mix all together; dissolve soda in boiling water and pour in baking pan.
It will be a little thin.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel candy
directions: Melt caramels and cream in double boiler or microwave.
Pour over cornflakes, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core, and slice apples.
Pour lemon juice over them. Combine apples, sugar, and water in a large skillet.
Cover and cook slowly
until tender.	Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg into mixture.
Let stand until cool.
Pour into unbaked pie crust that has been sprinkled with bread crumbs.
Dot apples with the butter. Place upper crust over filling and prick with fork.
Seal crusts well with fork dipped in flour.
Brush entire top of pie with milk.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes until browned.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushroom in 2 tablespoons butter; salt and pepper to taste, add 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Add to the first 3 ingredients.
Mix, then add the Cheddar cheese.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
May require more milk.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight or 2 to 3 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut firm, mature green tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Coat each side with flour seasoned with salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Place in skillet containing hot oil to which you have added 1 pat of butter.
Fry until coating is crisp, several minutes on each side.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Fry pork chops in pan with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine. Cook rice.
After the pork chops are done, take the chopped onions and the other tablespoon butter or margarine and fry up the onions in the same pan that the pork chops were in.
This will give your onions the flavor of the pork chops.
Take the cooked rice and onions and mix them together, placing them in a nice casserole dish.
Place your pork chops on top.
Serves 6 to 8.
Takes 20 to 30 minutes to fix.

title: swiss bliss (steak)
directions: Spread center of large sheet of foil with oleo.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Arrange on foil slightly overlapping. Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bring foil up over and double fold edges to seal tightly.
Bake for 2 hours at 375°.

title: crab stuffed crepes
directions: In bowl, combine milk, flour, eggs and salt; beat until smooth.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
For each crepe, pour 3 to 4 tablespoons of batter into hot lightly greased 7-inch crepe pan, turning to coat bottom of pan with batter.
Cook until golden brown.
Remove and keep warm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter; stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: country pickles
directions: Let stand 24 hours before using.
Will last up to 6 months in refrigerator.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream margarine, cocoa, and sugar together.
Then add eggs one at a time beating well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder and salt, add pecans.
Batter will be thick.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 10 x 13.
After baking 30 minutes pour marshmallows over hot cookies, and spread topping over marshmallows.

title: butter roca(candy)
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart pan. Remove from heat and blend in sugar.
Cook until mixture bubbles. Add water and syrup and cook to 290° (use candy thermometer). Stir in nuts.
Pour on lightly buttered cookie sheet or marble slab.
Cool to room temperature. Keep loosening with spatula to prevent sticking.
Melt 1/2 of the chocolate or chocolate bits.
Spread on top side of candy.
When chocolate is firm, turn underside up and spread with remaining chocolate.
When chocolate is completely firm, break candy into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Delicious!
Tastes like Heath bar candy.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion; put in salt water for 1 hour.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over drained onion and cucumbers.
Let set for several hours or overnight.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs and corn.
Add milk and melted butter; mix.
Stir in Jiffy mix.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: summer vegetable mix
directions: In skillet, add few teaspoons oil and cut yellow squash and zucchini, onion, garlic and tomatoes.
Cook until soft and serve over top of pasta.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion.
Drain.
Add chili sticks, chili beans, tomatoes, tomato juice, salt, pepper, chili powder and hot peppers.
Stir until chili sticks are smooth with other ingredients.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix together.
Makes 1 pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (pecans can be used instead of English walnuts).

title: heavenly dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in small bowl.
In large bowl, beat pudding and milk until thick.
Add vanilla in.
Then add cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Layer in planter pot the crushed cookies and nuts (if desired) with alternate layers of pudding mix.
Top with Oreos.
Insert a flower in pot to fool your guests.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar; set aside.
Peel and cut broccoli fine.
Mix broccoli, shredded cheese, crumbled bacon and onion.
Pour Miracle Whip mixture over salad.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: churros(long johns)
directions: Pour oil 1-inch deep into a 10-inch skillet.
Heat to 370°. Bring water to a boil in 2-quart saucepan.
Add butter and salt. Heat until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once; remove from heat.
Beat until mixture is smooth and is the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Turn mixture into a pastry bag fitted with a star tip.
Squeeze directly into hot oil, making Churros about 8-inches long.
Cook 3 or 4 at a time, until a deep golden brown; turn occasionally.
Drain over skillet, then on paper towels.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Thaw strawberries. Drain pineapple.
Mix these three items together, then mix Cool Whip in and freeze in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Thaw for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Put on a dish or pan the size of a pizza pan (round). mixed together. mixed together. Monterey Jack, shredded.

title: legendary lentil soup
directions: Saute
meat
in butter. Add stock, lentils, chilies and marjoram
and
simmer
about
30 minutes.
Saute vegetables in oil,
adding
garlic
at
the
end.
Add
to pot with meat and stock.
Melt
tablespoons
butter;
add 3 tablespoons flour and stir
until
light brown.	Whisk in 2 cups stock.	Add to large pot.
Add 4 tablespoons red wine vinegar, freshly ground pepper and salt to taste.	Simmer 30 minutes.
Adjust seasoning.
Serve with croutons and yogurt or sour cream.

title: lance's blue ribbon sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out in powdered sugar.
Cut into desired shapes and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: velveeta sausage dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage (drain).
Cube up Velveeta cheese.
Put hamburger, sausage and Velveeta cheese into a crock-pot.
Stir until cheese starts to melt; stir in fiesta nacho cheese soup.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta type of your choice.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix the soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over pasta.
Toss in vegetables and pepperoni.
Sprinkle to taste with Salad Supreme. Toss and chill before serving.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and mix all ingredients. Use enough chicken broth to cover the dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and leave in refrigerator all night.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beef 'n bean burger
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Stir in pork and beans, catsup, onion and mustard.
Simmer.

title: economy hominy and bean soup
directions: Heat all ingredients, except the cheese. Ladle into soup bowls and top with cheese.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine; mix well. Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread half of crumb mixture in baking dish.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
In 2-quart casserole dish, place sliced potatoes.
Add browned hamburger and onion on top of this.
In a separate bowl, take liquid from Veg-All and the tomato soup (undiluted) and mix together.
Veg-All should be layered on top of hamburger.
Top with soup mixture.
Place covered casserole dish in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are cooked.

title: italian sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients together well.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 1 to 2 days.
Use as you would any other sausage.

title: john's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add other ingredients and form into 2 small or 1 large cheese ball.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: steak-n-potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large skillet.
Cook on medium heat until done.
(Add water to bottom of skillet to keep food from sticking.)

title: quick chocolate peanut butter cookie pops(great for kids!)
directions: You will need 10 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat about 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: sweet cream and noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, sugar to taste and salt in large mixing bowl; stir well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate a couple of hours to blend flavors.

title: vi's chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and extract.
Add sugar.
Add flour with salt a little at a time to form a paste.
Form into rolls and chill overnight.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Sift spices and sugar together.
Combine all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake slowly at 300° until set.
Pie will appear solid.
Cool.

title: meo's cinnamon rolls
directions: Put mashed potatoes into a bowl; add sugar, shortening, salt and scalded milk.
Let stand until cold.
Add yeast, beaten eggs and flour.
Knead slightly until smooth.
Place in refrigerator to rise gradually.
Usually made at 9:00 a.m., ready to make into rolls at 4:00 p.m.
Let rise until ready to bake.
Roll out dough. Melt butter and spread.
Put brown sugar and sprinkle cinnamon. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut and put in muffin rings that have been prepared with brown sugar and nuts.
Cook at 350°.
Watch until brown.

title: pineapple casserole #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty 1 large can pineapple (undrained) into casserole dish.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Add layer of grated cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in one egg yolk at a time, beating thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture one tablespoon at a time to sugar and butter mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Beat the six egg whites; fold into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add well beaten eggs, evaporated milk, melted margarine, coconut, salt and vanilla.
Mix all of the ingredients well.
Bake in uncooked pie shells at 300° for 45 minutes.
This makes four 9-inch pies or three 9-inch deep dish pies.
This also freezes well.

title: cornflake bars
directions: Mix together sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
When mixed well, pour over cornflakes onto a cookie sheet.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: graham-mallow squares
directions: Beat the eggs and add sugar and margarine. Cook on low heat about 5 minutes or until it begins to thicken. Add the vanilla. Crush the graham crackers and combine with the marshmallows.
Pour filling (cooled) over cracker/marshmallow mix and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish. Chill overnight.
If desired, add 3/4 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup coconut.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta and fagioli
directions: Drain and rinse the beans and set aside.
Cook bacon until crispy; drain on paper towel and set aside.
Saute garlic, onion and celery until tender.
Add the tomato sauce, water, basil, bay leaves, salt and pepper and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add the beans and bacon that has been crumbled up and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.

title: old fashioned spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and mushroom.
Add other ingredients.
Cook (simmer) 2-4 hours.
Remove bay leaves and serve.
Serves 4.

title: crispy date bars
directions: Combine ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Press into an 11 x 7-inch or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple butter(made in oven)
directions: Put all ingredients in roasting pan and cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir several times to mix spices.
Put in blender, jar and seal.

title: chicken apple salad with cashews
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cashews.
Add mayonnaise until desired consistency.
Stir in cashews before serving.

title: sour cream penuche
directions: Combine sugar and cream; heat to boiling, stirring until sugars are dissolved.
Add butter; cover and cook over low heat 3 or 4 minutes.
This dissolves any sugar crystals on the sides of the pan and keeps the candy from sugaring.
Remove cover and boil to 236° (soft ball).
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into greased pan and let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen large pieces or 1 1/3 pounds.

title: "hula" sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a well-greased baking dish (Pam may be used).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with topping.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except parsley flakes.
Shape in ball; sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Beat strawberries, egg whites, sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl at high speed for 15 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease one large or 2 small Pyrex dishes with oleo.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs to cover bottom of dish.
Save half for top.
Spoon mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
(Ground walnuts may be added too.)
Cover and chill.
Serves 2.

title: methodist salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours; ready to serve.

title: flounder in spinach(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook and drain spinach.
Mix together sour cream, onion, flour, lemon juice and salt.
Add half of this mixture to spinach.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as usual; drain.
Melt butter.
Blend flour, milk, salt, pepper and onion (jar).
Cook and stir until thick. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix macaroni in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle in croutons or bread crumbs.
Bake at about 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken matok(sweet chicken)
directions: Spread pieces of chicken in single layer of roasting pan. Sprinkle in this order:
garlic, salt, soy sauce, ginger, honey, brown sugar, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: tuna patties
directions: Note:
Need 2 tablespoons vegetable oil for frying.

title: kitty chow
directions: Pour cereal into a large roasting pan.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter in microwave.
Pour mixture over cereal; stir until coated.
Put 2 cups powdered sugar in a large brown grocery bag.
Pour in cereal mixture, then add 2 more cups of powdered sugar.
Shake until cereal is coated.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken  stir-fry
directions: Mix teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, ginger root or five spice powder.
Cut chicken in pieces, approximately 1/2 x 2-inch, and marinate in above sauce while preparing veggies.
Chop or slice all veggies.
Heat wok or frypan; put oil in after pan is hot. Add chicken to pan (saving marinade).
Stir-fry chicken 4 to 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Add veggies to pan and cook 4 to 5 minutes; add chicken to pan.
Mix leftover marinade with applesauce and add to pan.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes to thicken sauce.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Remove ginger slices before serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature before mixing. Mix grated cheese and margarine with mixer until you can see no cheese particles.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in Rice Krispies with fork.
Roll in finger shapes and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lisa's squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt and sugar.
Simmer with small amount of water for 20 minutes.
Drain and mash with potato masher.
Add eggs, melted butter, flour, milk and cheese.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Top with bread crumbs and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
(Freezes well, uncooked.)

title: pot roast
directions: Place pot roast in a roasting pan, can be frozen, pour in the water. Add bouillon cubes, liquid smoke and onions to the water. Bake at 225°f. 110°c. gas mark 1/4 for 4-6 hours. Remove from oven, add potatoes, return to the oven and bake for a further 2 hours. Roast should be tender and fall apart. Baste periodically during cooking time. Shread the beef on a platter to serve.

title: deep fried jalapeno peppers
directions: Fill peppers with cheese, dip in beaten egg, roll in batter and deep fry.

title: italian ricotta pie
directions: In a separate bowl, mix 3 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/2 cup milk.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and Ricotta cheese well, then add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat with beaters.
Add cornstarch and milk mixture to mixing bowl.
Put into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Lower the temperature to 375° and bake another 45 minutes or until brown or until testing with a knife to see if it comes out dry.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with a little cinnamon.

title: wiener schnitzles
directions: Take egg roll wrap, place on it 1 slice of cheese and then wrap around each individual wiener.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: easy italian pork dinner
directions: Marinate pork chops in salad dressing for 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chops from marinade.
Brown chops on both sides in oil over medium heat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Return browned chops to marinade in baking dish.
Layer potatoes and onion over chops.
Dot with butter.
Drizzle with remaining 2 tablespoons dressing.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes and chops are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken succotash stew
directions: Cook bacon in 8 quart Dutch oven over medium high heat until browned.
Remove bacon to paper towels to drain.
Spoon off all but 1 Tbsp. bacon drippings.
Cut chicken into bite sized pieces. Combine flour and salt, coat chicken with flour mixture.
Cook chicken in drippings until browned.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, corn, beans, bouillon and 3 c. hot water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 6 servings. About 285 calories per serving.

title: monster mouth snack
directions: Take quartered apples and spread peanut butter on slices.
Take 3 to 4 marshmallows and place on top of peanut butter.
Take another slice of apple and put on top.
When finished you should have a mouth made of all ingredients.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/3 cup French onion soup with beef, crumbs and egg. Make 6 patties.
Brown patties.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over patties.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.

title: wisconsin broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Add cooked, crumbled bacon, cheese and onion.
Mix salad dressing; add sugar and vinegar.
Toss onto salad.
Serve or refrigerate.

title: brunch eggs california
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute corn in butter until just tender. Set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add cooled corn and mix.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 1 hour or until firm and golden on top.
Serve with sour cream, tomatoes, guacamole and salsa.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry-melon salad
directions: Cut melons in half and remove seeds.
Use melon baller to scoop out the pulp.
Line melon shells with leaf lettuce.
Divide melon balls among lined shells.
Mount 1/3 cup cottage cheese in center of each.
Place 1/4 cup strawberries around each mound. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cut beef bacon into 1-inch pieces and cook until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Combine and stir into drippings the sugar, onion, flour and celery seed.
Gradually add water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add cooked and cubed potatoes and bacon pieces.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad (orange)
directions: Place cottage cheese in mixing bowl. Mix in box of Jell-O (orange) powder mixture. Mix in the Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Beat oil and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients and add with vanilla, carrots, pineapple and nuts to the sugar mixture.

title: homemade tomato catsup
directions: Measure spices into saucepan. Add vinegar. Cover.
Heat to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand while you prepare tomato mixture (spices steep in vinegar like tea).
Peel the tomatoes. Place in kettle and mash.
Add onion and red pepper.
Heat to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put tomatoes through food mill or coarse sieve.
Add sugar.
Heat to a boil, then simmer briskly.
Cook until you have only half the amount you began with.
(May measure with a ruler.)
It will take about 45 to 60 minutes to get to this stage.
Strain vinegar and spices directly into tomato mixture. Discard spices. Add salt.
Simmer to consistency you like for catsup.
Stir often. Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add rest of ingredients.
Beat with mixer until creamy.

title: candy apples
directions: Use candy thermometer at 300° (hard crack).
Fun for parties and kids to eat.

title: longley potatoes
directions: Peel, cut and boil potatoes 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain well. While the potatoes are warm, beat in the other ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart covered casserole at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: aunt jenny's brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, honey and corn syrup. Mix well. Sift flour, salt and cocoa together and add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a jelly roll pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until top is a dull crust and a slight imprint remains when lightly touched with finger.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into baking dish.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Add flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and margarine to first ingredients; simmer until thick.
Spread mixture over half of the pie crust.
Fold over after brushing edges with mixture of 1 egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Brush top of crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Sift together sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Blend egg yolks and water; stir into sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter and lemon juice and peel.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: fruit dessert pizza
directions: Chill fruits (not bananas).
Slice dough thin.
Place on 14-inch pizza pan.
Press together to form thin layer of dough. Bake at 325° for approximately 12 minutes or until brown.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together.
Spread over cookie dough.
Drain fruit well.
Save pineapple juice to soak bananas in to prevent browning.
Arrange fruit; top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Nuts are optional.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, then add flour and sugar that have been mixed together.
Add corn, milk and margarine; mix well.
Pour into microwave-safe dish; microwave 15 minutes on High.
(Can be baked at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.)

title: su casa chili
directions: Sear beef in heavy pot until brown, 3 minutes.
Turn heat to simmer and add 1 cup of water, the chili powder, cumin, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Stir to blend and simmer, covered half an hour.
Now add the onion and garlic.
Simmer another 1/2 hour. Brown the flour in the oil in a skillet.
Stir in 2 cups of water until blended.
Then add to chili pot.
Lower heat and cook a few minutes more.
It's now ready to eat.

title: butter dips
directions: Stir and mix ingredients.
Melt margarine and mix with three previous ingredients.
Knead dough 15 to 20 times on a lightly floured board.
Cut and roll in melted butter.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Serve with jam or honey.

title: fireman's stew
directions: In electric skillet, crumble ground chuck evenly over bottom. Season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Spread onion slices evenly over meat.
Next, add potatoes evenly on onion, and then carrots over potatoes.
Spread soup over the top of carrots.
Cover and cook approximately 30 minutes at 250°, or until meat is done.
Do not stir during cooking time!!!
Serve in layers.
Will serve 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Butter a 1 qt. baking dish.
Drain spinach and squeeze out moisture.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Be sure cabbage and carrots are chopped up into fine pieces. Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice in a large bowl and beat until smooth.
Add cabbage, carrots and onion and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: meat pot pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; add tomato sauce, chili powder, hot sauce, olives and salt.
Stir and cook briefly.
Add chopped green pepper and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with pie crust or biscuits and bake until brown in a 425° oven.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread dip on platter.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning and spread on dip.
Chop onions and tops; put on top of that.
Chop tomatoes and put on top of that.
Grate cheese and put on top of that.

title: sidney's brown sugar pecans
directions: Mix sugar, flour and beaten egg.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pecans until well coated.
Lay out individually on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave pecans in it for an additional 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler. Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt into a saucepan and slowly stir in milk.
Cook until mixture thickens and becomes bubbly.
Blend in chocolate. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts. Chill.
Makes 1 cup.
Contains 22 calories per tablespoon.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wash and remove seeds from pepper before grinding.
Combine pepper, sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Bring to high rolling boil. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Yields 3 pints.

title: hawaiian zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, sugar and cinnamon; stir in pecans. In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.
Mashed bananas may be substituted for zucchini to make delicious Banana Nut Bread.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients together. Add to greased dish. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: batter fried chicken breasts
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix egg and milk together in shallow bowl. Add 2 tablespoons flour and mix until very smooth. Dip each chicken piece in batter.
Dip chicken in remaining flour until well coated.
Heat oil in heavy frying pan to 375°.
Fry 4 or 5 chicken pieces together for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in a
250° oven until all chicken is fried.

title: quick chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings. Takes only 20 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Prepare fryer as usual; salt and pepper.
Slightly beat egg and add milk.
Mix well.
Put about 1 1/2 cups instant potato flakes.
Melt oleo in pan or dish that can be put into oven.
Roll chicken in milk and egg mixture then in instant potatoes.
Lay chicken in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients three times.
Add this and pineapple or juice alternately.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Place ground beef in 3 qt. microwave-proof casserole; break up with fork.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes, or until beef is no longer red, stirring once during cooking time.
Break up ground beef again with fork; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on High 27 to 30 minutes, or until mixture boils and noodles are cooked, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf before serving.
8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, until edges are golden brown. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: honey roasted peanuts
directions: Heat a cookie sheet in oven at 325° for 10 minutes.
Melt stick of margarine on cookie sheet.
Combine egg whites and sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold nuts into mixture.
Place on cookie sheet in oven for 1/2 hour.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Fold Cool Whip and yogurt together; set aside.
Layer half each of the cake, yogurt, strawberries and kiwi in an 8-inch square dish.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: olympic chicken
directions: In a wok, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil over high heat until hot, swirling to coat both sides of pan.
Add chicken and stir-fry until cooked through but still juicy, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove to plate.
In same wok, heat remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil over high heat.
Add onion, garlic, oregano and bell peppers; stir-fry until soft, 3 to 5 minutes.
Return chicken to wok.
Add orange juice and mandarin oranges and their juice.
Cook until liquid is slightly reduced, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: salmon party ball(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Mix nuts and parsley.
Coat ball with mixture.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: (I use self-rising flour and omit baking powder and salt.)

title: ranch macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream and macaroni.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts and mixture begins to thicken. Fold in sour cream.
Add macaroni.
Cook until heated thoroughly.

title: "don't peek" five hour beef stew
directions: Mix together in roaster.
Cover tightly.
(Seal with aluminum foil if necessary.)
Bake at 250° for five hours.
Don't peek for five hours!

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Do not drain pineapple.
Mix together in one bowl.
Bake on sheet pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: traditional matzo brei *
directions: Pour warm water over matzo.
Drain, squeezing out water. Beat eggs and seasonings and stir together with the matzo.
Heat oil and fry matzo mixture on both sides until golden.
Serve sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar and spread with jam.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix dates, nuts, candy and coconut with 1/2 cup flour.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients and add date mixture.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until done. (Use 2 loaf pans.)

title: apple cider punch
directions: Mix all together. Simmer 20 minutes. Float with orange slices. Serve hot.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Get a large frying pan and place the vegetable oil and butter in it, but do not melt yet.
Rinse off tomatoes.
Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Beat egg in a small mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine the corn meal (or flour), salt and pepper.
Place this last mixture in a shallow bowl (wide cereal or soup size).
Dip the tomatoes in the egg batter first, then coat the tomato with the corn meal (or flour) mixture.

title: macaroni saute
directions: All is cooked together in 1 skillet!

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash and dry scallops.
Beat egg, water, salt and pepper.
Dip scallops in this mixture, then roll in crushed crackers.
Place scallops in buttered pie plate.
Pour melted butter over scallops and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: ham rolls
directions: Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Add chipped olives, relish and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Spread on slice of ham at one side lengthwise and roll up ham.
Secure with toothpick.
May leave whole or cut into smaller rolls for hors d'oeuvres.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order listed in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Put Cool Whip on top.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix together.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute butter, onions and garlic.
Add paprika, salts, tomato, green pepper and stock.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and cover.
Cook for 40 minutes at medium-high heat.
Add water or more stock if necessary.
Add flour with light cream slowly; stir and cook until you have a thick gravy.
Add sour cream (do not let boil) and serve.
Serves 4.

title: cattle king potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender with salt and garlic clove.
Mash well with butter.
Add egg yolks, cream, mushrooms and parsley. Pile into baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.
Can be made ahead and baked at the last minute.

title: crunchy ham ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
(May use food processor.) Mix in
next 5 ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour or 2. Form into ball; roll in nuts.
Serve with Ritz or wheat crackers. You may chop
the
ham in your food processor also. This is very popular
at
parties,
especially
at
holidays. Serves 8 or 10.

title: cauliflower delight
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Mix milk, butter and flour in medium pan until it boils.
Thicken mix with handfuls of grated Mozzarella cheese.
Place cooked cauliflower in greased casserole pan.
Pour milk mixture over top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: low-sodium, low-fat lasagna
directions: Heat the vegetable oil in a large saucepan.
Saute the onion, garlic and green pepper until softened.
Add the ground round and pepper.
Cook until meat loses its red color.
Drain off excess fat.
Add the tomato sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, parsley and bay leaves.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until sauce has thickened.
While cooking, if sauce becomes too thick, add small amounts of water as needed.
Prepare the lasagna noodles according to the package without salt.
You do not have to use oil to prevent sticking as directed on some packages.
Gently stir noodles occasionally.
They will not stick.
Cook noodles for 10 to 12 minutes or until al dente (still a bit chewy).

title: smoothies
directions: Puree in blender until smooth and serve.
Makes 3 medium servings at 130 calories per serving.

title: bambi's pasta sauce
directions: You can substitute crushed, chunk and fresh diced tomatoes with tomato/basil/garlic etc. tomatoes, whatever you like.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
the
butter
and sugar.	Add eggs and beat well. Mix in	remaining ingredients.	Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet;
flatten
out
and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. (Batter will be real stiff.)

title: crisp orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and flavorings; mix well. Sift together flour, soda and salt; mix with first mixture.
Then stir in milk.
Dip hands in flour and form dough into small balls; place on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten with a flat bottom glass dipped in sugar as each cookie is pressed.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Stir well, let stand for 24 hours. Pour into freezer cartons and freeze. Thaw and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shell.
Bake until firm at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°. The sauce makes an excellent gravy for rice. Serves 6.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook until tender; drain and mash. Add melted oleo, milk, catsup, beaten egg yolks, salt and pepper and stir.
Add flour to cracker crumbs and mix.
Add onion, cheese and crumbs.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stir in mixture. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until brown.
Squash may be substituted for the eggplant.

title: easy chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a Pyrex dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch).
Place chicken in dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes more.
Mix soup, water and sage.
Pour over chicken and bake 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix in a 2-quart saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water, salt and chocolate.
Cut in pieces.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and beat in margarine and vanilla.

title: shake 'n bake(coating for chicken and chops)
directions: Store in tightly covered container.
Use 1/3 cup per pound.

title: chocolates
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients (except paraffin and chocolate pieces).
Form mixture into small balls.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Stir constantly until melted.
With toothpicks, inserted into balls, dip into chocolate mixture. Refrigerate until cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together and put into casserole.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: basic bread stuffing(enough dressing for 12 pounds turkey)
directions: *I use dressing bread from bakery.

title: rouladen
directions: Cut each round steak in three pieces.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Add chopped onion and 1/2 strip of bacon to each piece of steak.
Roll meat lengthwise; secure with toothpicks or skewers. Brown meat on all sides and put in small roasting pan.
Add enough water to about half cover meat.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours (turn a couple of times to keep top from drying out).
Take meat from roaster and use a thickener to make a gravy from broth. (You can use sirloin tip in place of round steak.)
Serves 6.

title: verna maes' apple crunch
directions: Boil together pie filling and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour into long buttered baking dish.
Add cake mix.
On top, add pecans and melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown, usually 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham smothered in sweet potatoes
directions: Cut ham 3/4 inch thick and into serving-sized pieces and brown slightly on both sides.
Arrange over the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Cover with sweet potatoes, add hot water and melted butter, and sprinkle with sugar.
(a little powdered cinnamon may be added if desired).
Cover and bake in hot oven (400 degrees) for 45-50 minutes or until the potatoes are cooked and ham is tender. Uncover and let brown attractively before serving in the baking dish.

title: potato pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in custard.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Put vegetables in large shallow dish.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Cover.
Chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain. Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and salt together and bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat; add oats.
If	desired,
add 1/2 cup peanut butter or a few nuts, raisins or coconut.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: ritz dessert
directions: Crush crackers, butter and sugar in food processor.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save small amount for the top.

title: disappearing party bites
directions: Take a piece of bread and spread cream cheese on it with a table knife.
Take sunflower seeds and press them into the cream cheese.
Cut into four triangles.
Serve.

title: seafoam drops
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and hot water.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, without stirring, until syrup forms hard ball in cold water.
Pour slowly over slightly beaten egg whites, beating constantly, until stiff enough to hold a swirl.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased pan.

title: glurch
directions: Mix glue, starch and food coloring.
Mix using your hands. Mixture may appear as if it won't combine.
Do not give up.
Keep for up to a month in refrigerator in a covered container.

title: sugar coated nuts
directions: Cook sugar, water and cinnamon until dissolved.
Add pecans. Layer, single layer best for baking.
Bake on cookie sheet. Lightly salt nuts and stir.
Bake 10 minutes.
Stir.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 2 cups of Cool Whip.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients (except tortillas).
Spread 1/4 cup on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Chill.
Cut in 3/4 to 1-inch slices. Enjoy.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix like pie crust and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white christmas fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately the milk and vanilla. Fold in egg whites; pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine ingredients together and chill.

title: rice and grave
directions: To fix this meal I would need 2 eggs and a brop of salt and a brop of pepper and a pan.

title: best-ever crab cakes
directions: Carefully pick over crab meat, removing all shells.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Form into cakes and brown in butter until golden and crispy.

title: apple-banana pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Combine peels and juices. Add apples and bananas; combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon. Turn into pie shell.
Cut remaining pastry into strips and weave lattice fashion over top of pie.
Trim edges; flute.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In at least a 5-quart pot, brown hamburger in a small amount of water.
I separate the hamburger by stirring it with a fork as it browns.
Add tomato juice, vegetables, etc. and seasonings. Simmer for at least an hour to blend the flavors and spices.

title: mexican cheese soup
directions: Cut tortillas in half, then slice into 1/4-inch strips.
Fry tortillas in 1/4-inch hot oil in a skillet until crisp, but not brown.
Drain oil, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until onions are tender.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil; serve warm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cool sausage and cheese to room temperature.
Mix with bisquick forming a dough.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 275 for 25 minutes.

title: creamy velvet fudge
directions: In
a
1 1/2-quart glass casserole, microwave chocolate chips for
2 minutes on High, rotate 1/4 turn halfway through cooking. Stir until smooth.	Blend in milk, vanilla, powdered sugar	and salt.
Add	nuts;
blend
well.
Pour
into an 8 x 12-inch	wax paper lined dish.
Chill until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Serve on bed of lettuce. Garnish with additional sliced bananas and avocado that have been dipped in lemon juice.

title: melange salad(wonderful!)
directions: Divide lettuce between 4 large salad plates.
Arrange palm, asparagus and red pepper pieces in pinwheel pattern over lettuce. Place 1/2 of the artichoke hearts in center of each pinwheel. Sprinkle each salad with olives and shrimp.
Spoon dressing over salad.

title: indiana buttermilk pie
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Put oven rack on lower third of oven.

title: date balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and dates in heavy boiler and boil on low/medium for 7 to 8 minutes, until thickened. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and nuts. Wait until cool enough to handle and roll into balls. Place on wax paper.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal cutlets between two sheets of wax paper.
Season veal pieces with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dust lightly with flour; shake off excess.

title: butterscotch rocky road
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter in large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave for about 5 minutes on Medium, just until melted.
Stir and fold in marshmallows and peanuts.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan; line with wax paper.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut a thin slice from stem end of each pepper and remove seeds and membranes.
Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers.
Cook 5 minutes and drain. Mix remaining ingredients.
Stuff and stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Good with baked potatoes.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Wash okra, leaving tops on.
Parboil 2 minutes in salted water and drain well.
Slice tops off okra pods and slit lengthwise. Dip in egg (beaten with one tablespoon of water).
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Dip okra in corn flake mixture and place in shallow buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Place cooked rice in a casserole dish.
Place broccoli on top of rice.
Pour soup on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle with chopped onion. Pour melted Cheez Whiz on top of onion and top it all with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jared jack
directions: Butter both pieces of bread and toast slightly under the broiler.
Turn over to untoasted side of bread and lay pieces of cheese on one of the slices.
Fry bacon or ham and place on other piece of toast.
Also fry egg and burst the yolk.
Place on top of bacon.
Bring both sides together to form a sandwich.
Enjoy!

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix corn bread mix according to directions.
Add cream-style corn.
Scramble and drain hamburger, sausage and onion.
Mix mushroom soup and water together well.

title: chewy oatmeal freezer cookies
directions: Mix sugars; add margarine, then eggs and oats.
This will be a very stiff batter (your arm will feel like it's going to fall off) or use heavy duty mixer (small mixer not strong enough).
Form into 3 or 4 rolls; wrap and freeze.
When ready to bake, thaw 10 to 15 minutes, then cut in slices.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wax paper.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add peanut butter, stir until mixed well.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Add oats, mix fast and drop on waxed paper until set.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots; cool.
Slice onion and pepper and mix with drained, cooled carrots.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Marinate overnight or longer.
Drain and serve. Keep in refrigerator.

title: t. j. shake
directions: Stir; cook in microwave 3 to 5 seconds.
Stir again.
Serve with straw and spoon.
Makes 1 serving.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the butter.
Layer coconut over the crumbs.
Layer chocolate chips.
Layer butterscotch chips.
Layer nuts.
Layer peanut butter.
Spoon Eagle Brand milk over this, then fill the can with plain milk and mix well.
Finish pouring over layers. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut in squares.
Rich but good.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Place all ingredients in a baking dish and bake about 30 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Add chilies.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
In an 8-inch square pan, spread beans.
Top with meat mixture, sour cream mixture and avocado dip.
Cover and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix cornbread, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Stir in milk, eggs and shortening.
Pour into greased 9 X 12 in baking pan.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand until cool. Crumble into bowl.
Stir in bacon, onion and tomato.
Fold in just enough mayonnaise to coat.

title: snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first nine ingredients.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt the butter.
Add the seasonings; stir until dissolved.
Pour over cereal mixture; stir to coat.
Place in large greased roasting pans.
Bake, uncovered at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Soak tortillas in tomato juice for 1 minute.
Put turkey or chicken mixture in tortilla and roll, about 2 tablespoons.
Put in greased casserole dish. Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turnips and carrots
directions: Heat oil; add cut onions, carrots and turnips.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add salt and sugar.
Serve hot.

title: wine cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil, sherry and nutmeg.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, orange juice and oil.
Drizzle over cake while cake is still warm.
Moist cake; freezes well.

title: baked egg dish
directions: Butter bread with crusts on and cube.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add ham.
Spread cubed bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over.
Spread with cheese.
Cover dish with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: 1. Remove potato pulp from halved potatoes. Reserve skins. 2. Mix pulp, margarine, milk, mayonaise, cottage cheese, chives, salt, and pepper together.
3. Spoon mixture into potatoes skins and sprinkle cheese
on top.
4.eat oven to 400°. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: lemon lime sky high pie
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Beat egg yolks with lime juice, lemon juice and water. Stir with gelatin mixture. Place over boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly (about 6 minutes). Add lemon and lime rind. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and beat until very stiff. Fold in gelatin mixture. If necessary, chill until it will pile. Turn into baked pie shell. Chill until firm; garnish with whipped cream.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix pie filling, drained pineapple and sugar and put in refrigerator overnight or 1 hour in freezer.
Add rest of ingredients and stir gently.
Chill.

title: bessie's corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cock-n-bull stew
directions: Just layer ingredients as listed.
Place in a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot (low 7 to 10 hours or high 4 hours).
Stir well before serving.
If you like a thick gravy, make a smooth paste with 1/4 cup flour and juices from stew.
Stir into crock-pot and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve with warm Italian or French bread.

title: stew meat casserole
directions: Put ingredients into crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve over noodles, rice or toast.

title: chest bars
directions: Put in another bowl and mix together.
Pour on top of bottom layer and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: asbury oyster fritters
directions: Add baking soda to oysters and mix well.
Add milk and then add flour, baking powder and meal, sifted together.
Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Fry in an iron frying pan in plenty of hot oil.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet cook hamburger and onion until tender; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Heat through. Remove from heat.
Beat eggs, stir in milk.
Add small amount of tomato sauce mixture to egg mixture.
Stir constantly.
Stir in kidney beans, then 1 1/2 cups Monterey Jack cheese and crushed taco shells.
Turn into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, remaining cheese, tomato and olives.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: crusty oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in margarine, then in mixture of cracker crumbs, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Place on foil lined shallow pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes 2 (8 ounce) containers.
Great with Wheat Thins.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix well all ingredients including beets.
Cook on low temperature, stirring constantly until thick.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of fat.
Saute onions and pepper in fat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage, pepper and onion.
Spread in pie crust shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until you can tell it is set in the center. Bake at 375°.

title: sour cream pound cake(optional:  pecan cake)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening (butter).
Beat egg yolks and add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add to mixture, stirring in sour cream alternately with the flour mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold in lightly.
If using pecans, fold in now. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large dish, layer ingredients, one at a time, in order given:
lettuce, green pepper, celery, onion, peas, mayonnaise, brown sugar, cheese and bacon bits.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serve in bowl.
Will keep 1 or 2 days, if necessary.

title: sweet sour red cabbage
directions: Put shredded cabbage in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain. Place in pan; add all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If too watery, remove lid.

title: island memories
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Melt oleo in iron skillet in oven. Add shrimp and garlic.
Broil until shrimp are pink.
Remove shrimp and set aside.
