Add onion and pepper.
Broil until tender, but crisp, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat until hot. Salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare rice according to directions. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread pudding #2
directions: Butter or spray a baking dish.
Add all mixed ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with cream or plain.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place chocolate chips in bottom of pie shell and top evenly with layer of pecans. Melt butter over medium heat. Remove from heat; cool 2 minutes. Stir corn syrup, sugar and eggs into melted butter. Pour on top of pie. Bake 45 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust from bread; butter 4 slices.
Grease 8-inch baking dish (cake pan).
Put 4 buttered slices in dish, cover with 1/2 the cheese; put on other 4 slices of bread and add remaining cheese.
In bowl, beat eggs and milk well; add salt.
Pour over bread, cover with foil and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken curry rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Put into greased baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and brown 30 minutes longer.

title: wide noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain off fat.
In another pan, combine tomatoes, cornstarch, sugar and allspice and cook until thickened.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain off water.

title: cheese biscuits(like red lobster's biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk, and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes in 450° oven until golden brown.
Mix butter, garlic powder, and parsley; melt on low in microwave oven.
Brush garlic mixture over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
(like Red Lobster's)
Serve warm. Serves 4 - 6.

title: roquefort cream dressing
directions: Combine the above ingredients and mix well.
Or place them in a pint jar and shake well.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Add Velveeta and 1 stick margarine to the broccoli.
Crumble crackers and mix with 1 stick melted margarine.
Spray 9x12 pan and pour broccoli and cheese on the bottom, top with crackers, and bake to warm at 350 for 15-20 minutes.

title: cherry almond cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cookie crumbs, 1 tablespoon sugar and the margarine; press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan (if using a larger pan, cook the cheesecake less than 1 hour).
Bake 10 minutes, cool.

title: oatmeal and rice krispy cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift together second 4 and add to first.
Then add vanilla, oatmeal and Rice Krispies.
Cut mixture into quarters and wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Chill.
Slice into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator. Great for last minute guests.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour in spring-form pan (lined with graham cracker crust mixture).
Start in cold oven.
When temperature reaches 325°, start timing.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let cool overnight.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain juices off pineapple and oranges.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Serve.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: For vegetables, can use frozen mixtures.

title: bruschetta
directions: Drizzle 1 teaspoon of oil on each slice of bread. Bake 8 minutes or until brown at 375°. Mix remaining ingredients and spoon on bread. Serve at room temperature.

title: cream tuna and peas
directions: Use rice as main dish using any seasoning you like when cooking.
Put tuna in a pot, breaking it in pieces.
Add mushroom soup and mix well.
Heat on slow.
Heat until hot.
Cook frozen peas; drain.
That's it!
Serve in bowl or soup bowls and put rice in first.
Add peas and then the tuna mix.
Enjoy!

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread diced ham over bottom of pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cheeses, reserving 3 to 4 tablespoons for top of quiche.
Lightly beat eggs with a wire whisk.
Add half and half and seasonings; blend until smooth.
Set the pastry shell on a cookie sheet and carefully add custard mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheeses.

title: favorite layer bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and egg, mixing until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with combined coconut, nuts and chocolate.
Press lightly into surface.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Grease bottom
and sides of a 9-inch square baking pan. Melt butterscotch
pieces
and
margarine
in
heavy
3-quart saucepan over
medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool to
lukewarm.
Add
next
6 ingredients to butterscotch
mixture in
saucepan;
mix
well.
Fold marshmallows, chocolate pieces and nuts into butterscotch batter just until combined, about
5 strokes.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 20
to
25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will be jiggly but becomes firm upon cooling.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake the salmon; mix all ingredients.
Place in a buttered loaf pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firmly set.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve warm.

title: low country boil
directions: In very large pot bring water to boil.
Add crab boil (vary amount according to taste).
Add potatoes and return to boil. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sausage and onion and cook another 7 minutes.
Add corn and cook 7 more minutes.
Lastly add shrimp and turn cooker off; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain liquid off and dig in.

title: christmas (or anytime) cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine softened butter with sugar and cream. Add milk and flavoring. Stir in flour, candied cherries and pecans. Form in 2 rolls. Roll in coconut; wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.

title: popcorn peanut butter munch
directions: Spread out popcorn in large, shallow, roasting pan.
In heavy skillet or saucepan, stir together margarine, sugar and syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils. Stir in peanut butter.
Continue cooking without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn. Stir to coat.
Bake uncovered in 250° oven, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Turn out in large bowl and break apart.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat orange juice and add jello.
When cool, add buttermilk and chopped apricots.
Place in icebox.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and peppers.
Drain grease and add soups and 1 can water.
Add cheese; melt.
Mix cooked spaghetti and sauce together.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(You may top with more cheese if desired before you bake.)

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornmeal thoroughly.
Add meal last.
Mix well.
Put in loaf pan and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: Peel
cucumbers.
Slice thinly into large bowl.
Sprinkle with the
salt.	Let
stand for 1 hour.	Drain and squeeze cucumber slices
until
fairly
dry.
In
a	saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar,
parsley and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove pan from heat and let cool.	Marinate cucumbers in mixture for several hours and chill.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on buttered waxed paper.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Use a very large flat tray to serve.

title: hot endive dressing
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, flour, vinegar and water and beat. Brown bacon.
Pour off grease.
Add egg mixture to bacon and cook until it thickens.
Pour over endive, lettuce or any other greens.

title: rice with chicken
directions: Season the chicken with the ingredients (pepper, salt, oregano and garlic).
Stir-fry the ham and bacon.
Then put in all the other ingredients, plus the chicken.
Stir-fry for 1/2 hour.
Add rice (uncooked) to chicken, mix it with stir-fry chicken and all other ingredients, then add the hot water (3 cups).
Keep at a boiling consistency and cover.
Once the water dried out, turn the rice over, lower flame and keep cooking until the rice is completely soft.

title: fantastic rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with celery and onions.
Drain off excess fat.
In a mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients and then pour it into a casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Rice absorbs sauce very well; if it looks dry, add more tomato sauce.

title: katie jo potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in potatoes and cheese. Top with Rice Krispies mixed with margarine.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Mix salt, pepper, water, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Drain all the juice from vegetables.
Toss vegetables and pour mixture over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Preheat a 9 x 13-inch oiled baking dish.
Pour 1/2 batter into dish and sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining batter over this and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs and separate.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Place browned spareribs in wok or large frypan.
Pour the mixed ingredients over the ribs and cook, covered, for about 15 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking for about 15 minutes or until the mixture is cooked down and glazes the ribs.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugar,
molasses
and egg together. Add dry ingredients
and mix well.
Roll into balls and dip in sugar, then re-roll.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: festive fall punch
directions: Heat 1 cup fruit drink with cinnamon candies; stir constantly until dissolved.
Combine with remaining juice in a large pitcher. Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup and add gelatine; remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and put in mold. Refrigerate. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Bake in
a
x
11-inch
baking dish.
Layer in order given. Lay
Tater Tots close together over top.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until brown.

title: old fashioned mincemeat bars
directions: Combine raisins and water (if using in place of mincemeat) and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salad oil.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray with Pam and flour pans.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. In medium bowl, beat eggs, orange juice and orange peel until blended.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well (if using fresh cranberries, fold them in when nuts are added).
Stir wet mixture into flour mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Gently stir in nuts.
Spoon evenly into loaf pans.
Bake for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in batter comes out clean.
Cool bread in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes. Then remove from pans.
Makes 3 loaf pans or 6 mini loaves.

title: fresh fruit dressing
directions: Blend sour cream and orange juice.
Mix pudding with milk and blend well.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix together in a slow cooker to keep warm.

title: clam dip for veggies
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Mix with rest of ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain grease if desired.
Add the vegetable soup and water.
Stir well and let boil.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring mix to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove.
Add chocolate mix to dry ingredients and beat at medium speed.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large pan, brown ground beef, stirring to break up meat. Drain off fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, onion, carrot, celery, barley, catsup, bouillon and spices, bringing to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender.
Season to taste.

title: scripture cake
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt.
Beat eggs and add baking powder and flour.
Add water and honey.
Put nuts and fruit through food chopper.
Add flour and fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix first six ingredients well until smooth, fold in blueberries.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Mix margarine, pecans and flour together and sprinkle over top of pie and bake another 10 minutes.

title: pick and peg cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Add oranges.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef and barley
directions: Rub salt and pepper into roast.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan or similar-sized wide casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients except parsley.
Pour around the meat and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
After 1 1/2 hours, turn meat over and add water if it seems too dry.

title: mexican fried okra
directions: Mix all ingredients, except okra, together for batter.
Stir in okra.
Use remainder of batter for cornbread.
Cook in skillet for stove or in covered glass bowl for microwave.
Cook until desired firmness.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add oil.
Mix all ingredients, adding carrots and nuts last.
Pour into three greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter rocks(for good gravy - no lumps!)
directions: Work with fingers.
Form into balls about size of a walnut. Chill.
Keep in refrigerator in plastic bag or covered jar.
One or more balls are needed for a cup of liquid.
If desired, make ahead and keep in fridge or even freeze.

title: lite turkey chili
directions: In a skillet, saute turkey and onion until turkey is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Mix well and pour over cabbage.
Place in jars.
Pack well and seal and tighten.

title: granola breakfast bread
directions: Grease two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Put 1/2 cup warm (105°) water in a mixing bowl and sprinkle the yeast over.
Stir and let stand to dissolve for 5 minutes. Add the 2 cups warm water, dry milk and butter; stir to blend. Beat in the salt, cornmeal and whole wheat flour and mix until smooth.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until well mixed.
Add as much more flour as needed to make a manageable dough. Add the granola. Turn the dough onto a floured board (or use dough hook of electric mixer) and knead for a minute.
Let dough rest 10 minutes. Resume kneading until the dough is elastic, about 5 more minutes.
Put the dough in a greased bowl and turn to coat all sides.
Cover and let rise to double its bulk.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
Shape into loaves and put in prepared pans.
Let rise to the tops of the pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until lightly browned and done. Cool on wire racks.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar real good.
Add salt and soda, then alternate eggs, flour and buttermilk.
Add vanilla last. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In 6-quart pot or saucepan combine butter, onion and celery; saute until light brown.
Add flour.
Continue stirring.
Add water and clam sauce.
Add potatoes.
Add milk, bay leaf and clams.
Add black pepper.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Press 1/2 to 3/4 into casserole.
Mix soup, chestnuts and sour cream.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread with meat
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain and set aside.
Combine corn meal, milk, salt, soda, bacon drippings, eggs and corn.
Grease large iron skillet.
Pour half of batter into skillet.
Add meat, green chilies and cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, broccoli, cauliflower, peppers, cucumbers, etc.

title: crock dill pickles
directions: Line crock with fresh grape leaves, fresh dill and fresh garlic bulb about the size of golf ball or use 1 tablespoon garlic powder. Bring water to a boil.
Shut off.
Add vinegar and salt.
Dissolve. Pour in crock over well scrubbed pickling cucumbers 3 to 4 inches long.
Put more leaves and dill over pickles.
Cover with dish and put a stone on the dish to keep pickles submerged or use bucket of water on dish.
Cover all with cloth so you won't get fruit flies. Takes 3 to 4 weeks.
The longer time is for larger cucumbers and the shorter time for smaller ones.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In microwave safe dish, combine soup and milk until blended. Stir in the potatoes, cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and cook in microwave on high for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cook for 10-12 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Stir and sprinkle with parmesan cheese if desired.

title: fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat butter then add sugar and almond paste, beat together then mix in flour to form dough.
Pat gently into the bottom of a 12-inch round or 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
When they are soft spread evenly and let cool.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, then 300° for 30 minutes.

title: thin spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook thin spaghetti in 3-quarts salted boiling water 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Brown beef and cook onion and pepper in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir to separate meat particles.
Add soups, water and garlic; heat.
Blend with 1/2 cup cheese and cooked thin spaghetti in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling and hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese and pimientos.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and pimientos over the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sunday pie
directions: Sweeten whip cream with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add sugar and salt to lightly beaten yolks.
Bring milk to boil.
Pour over first mixture gradually and cook in double boiler over medium heat. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin soaked in cold water.
Add vanilla and nutmeg and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into pastry shell or graham cracker crust. Beat cream and 1 teaspoon sugar, pour over the mixture and sprinkle on the grated chocolate.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Invert the other pie crust over top.
Seal edges.
Slit top of pie crusts. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes; serve.

title: no crust apple nut pie
directions: Combine egg and sugar.
Stir in next 5 ingredients (with spoon, no mixer).
Spoon into pie plate (greased and floured). Top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° preheated oven. Serve
warm with ice cream. Serves 6.

title: mints
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler.
Add peppermint oil and any color you wish to make mints.
Spoon into molds; refrigerate until firm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Stir in cream cheese. Butter 9x13 pan, roll out 1 can crescent rolls; pinch seams together. Spread sausage mixture on top. Cover with remaining can crescent rolls. Bake according to crescent rolls instructions.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine and unsweetened chocolate over medium-low heat. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in a greased square pan.
Yield:
1 dozen thick brownies.

title: smoky sausage corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in the rest.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry and orange salad
directions: Grind raw cranberries.
Add sugar and mix.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Grind apple and orange.
When gelatin mixture is cold and beginning to thicken, combine all ingredients and add gelatin.
Pour into a greased mold or individual molds and chill. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: molasses cookie cutouts
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat butter until fluffy and add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add egg and molasses; beat well and stir in dry ingredients.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Roll out small amounts of dough on floured board.
Cut into animal or other shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
When cool, decorate with white royal frosting.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Drain.
Add onion soup mix to water.
Add all other ingredients.
Add hamburger and bake for 30 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: country-fair cheesecake
directions: Early in day or day ahead, preheat oven to 325°.
In 9 x 2 1/2-inch spring-form pan, with hand, mix chocolate cookie crumbs, melted margarine or butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press mixture onto bottom of pan.

title: pink arctic frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise, sugar, cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Place paper muffin cups in muffin tins.
Fill with salad mixture.
Freeze. When frozen, they can be placed in a plastic bag and kept in freezer until ready to use.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: artichoke and spinach dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain all water from spinach. Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased casserole for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with crackers or bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and shred.
Cook rice as package directs.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and beat stiff.
Add sugar slowly, beating all the time until glossy.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful into greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven overnight or for at least 5 hours.

title: marinated vegetable italiano
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, except olives.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes or until veggies are tender-crisp.
Add olives.
Transfer to a bowl or storage container.
Cover.
Chill 6 hours or overnight. Makes about 9 cups.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine, pecans and coconut together; shape into balls.
Insert a toothpick in each ball, place on a dish and chill in the refrigerator until firm.
Melt the chocolate chips with the wax over low heat or over double boiler.
Dip each Coconut Ball into the chocolate and set out on a piece of wax paper for set up.

title: chicken cordon bleu(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add chicken and ham.
Cook until chicken is brown.
Stir in soup, water, beans and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and top with cheese; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Warm tortillas.
Place spoonful of chicken, green chile salsa, cheese and onion on tortilla. Roll up and place in baking dish. Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Warm soup and sour cream.
Pour over enchiladas. Sprinkle with cheese and dot with olives.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: "hot french cheese sandwiches"
directions: In a bowl, blend cheese and margarine.
Add eggs and salt. Whip until creamy.
Spread on bread slice; place another slice of bread on top and spread it with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika; cut into halves.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 400° oven. These may be frozen and then baked as needed.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour mixture in, mix cracker crumbs and grated cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a vegetable, but tastes like a dessert.
Everyone wants seconds!

title: peach dessert
directions: Use a 9-inch square cake pan.
Empty peaches and juice into baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mom's fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt
butter
in
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or
pan.
In
saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar is melted.
Cut
shortening
into
flour until crumbly. Add milk and stir
with	fork until dough leaves side of bowl. Roll dough into large
rectangle
1/2-inch thick on a floured board
after it has been kneaded until smooth.	Sprinkle fruit evenly
over
dough and roll up like jelly roll.
Slice dough into
16	slices 1/2-inch
thick.
Place
in
pan with melted butter.
Pour	sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Sift flour and soda together and set aside.
Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add flour and soda that has been sifted alternately with the buttermilk.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked lentils and cheese
directions: Combine lentils, water, spices, onion, garlic and tomatoes in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: halakahiki sausage
directions: Cut cooked sausage in bite-size pieces.
Combine pineapple and syrup, preserves and mustard in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add sausage; simmer 15 minutes.
Turn into chafing dish.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage and cheese on rye
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain.
Cube cheese and melt in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Spoon mixture onto rye bread.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes or until bread is toasted.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on medium heat until mixture bubbles.
Reduce to simmer.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot and left to remain warm serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in blender and blend.
Break bread into pieces and place in baking dish.
Add mix from blender, pulling some pieces of bread to top.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, sugar and onion; add milk and egg and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat (375°).
Fry only a few at a time until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.
Drain on absorbent towel.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix well; roll into small balls.
Bake at 450° about 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese pecan log
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup pecans; place on waxed paper.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients and shape into oblong roll.
Roll in remainder of pecans.
Can be refrigerated or served immediately.
Serve with crackers.
For best flavor, make one day in advance.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together. Stir in eggs and milk. Dip sliced onions. Cook in hot grease (375°) until golden brown.

title: cherry cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 2-quart bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup powdered sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Unroll crescent dough and reserve 4 triangles for decoration. Separate remaining dough into 12 triangles and arrange on 15-inch round stone with points toward center. Roll dough into a 14-inch circle. Cut out a 3-inch hole in center. Spread cream cheese mixture over dough to within 1/2-inch of edges. Top with pie filling. Roll remaining dough into a rectangle. Cut lengthwise into 12 strips. Twist strips and place in a spoke like fashion over filling. Press ends to seal at center and outer edges. Brush with egg white. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly.

title: browning quiche
directions: Crust:
Mix hash and bread crumbs thoroughly, then press into a large pie plate.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper, oregano, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, sauce and noodles, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: deer casserole
directions: Brown deer, then saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake and additional 30 minutes. Serve with a side dish of broccoli.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chicken fried steak bake
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces. Mix enough flour, salt and pepper to coat meat.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dredge meat through flour; dip into egg and milk, then back into flour.
Brown in skillet with oil.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, break onion slices into rings and spread out in pan.
Cover with browned steak pieces and pour beef broth over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: jean's pie crust(makes 13 double pie crusts or 26 individual crusts)
directions: Mix together Crisco, salt and cold water.
Gradually add into flour mixture.
Work in good with hands.
Can freeze in individual balls or roll into single shells or double crust.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, applesauce and oranges. Beat on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into two greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. In another mixing bowl, beat whipped topping, pineapple and pudding mix. Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange (with peel).
Add jello, dissolved with 1 cup of warm water.
Add sugar and liqueur.
Stir all together.
Cover for several days.
Add nuts just before serving. Really delicious.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss together ingredients lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in ungreased casserole and top with 1/2 cup broken chow mein noodles; drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
For 9 x 13-inch pan, double ingredients.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper and pour off grease.
Add one large can spaghetti sauce; mix together on low heat.
Add 1 teaspoon garlic powder, chili powder, red pepper and salt.

title: bread with sausage and cheese filling
directions: Thaw bread; mix cheeses.
Beat eggs; add cheeses.
Add to sausage that has been cooked and drained.
Mix well.
Roll out dough like a jelly roll.
Spread 1/2 the filling on each sheet of dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Put in greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix avocado, onion, chili, lemon juice, coriander and salt. Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of dip.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and cook rice until golden.
Stir in soup mix, water, soy sauce and browned meat.
Simmer for 25 minutes or until water is absorbed and rice is tender.
Make a hollow in the center of the rice and quickly stir eggs into it until set.
Mix with rice.

title: party rye appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on party rye.
Place under broiler until bubbly.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put in buttered baking dish. Dot with butter and cinnamon. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir a couple of times while baking.

title: tallorini
directions: In
large
bowl mix together ground beef, chili powder, onion, green
pepper
and salt and pepper; add to cooked spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and bake in flat dish in
350° oven for 25 minutes or until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs in a medium mixing bowl until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in sugar.
Add sour cream, raisins and pecans; blend well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes; cool.
Yield:
one 9-inch pie.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt until the size of a pea.
Beat egg and mix with water and vinegar.
Mix with flour mixture with a pastry mixer or a fork until flour is worked in.
Add a little more water, if needed.
Roll out and transfer to a pie pan.

title: ham logs
directions: Have your butcher grind ham and pork together.
Add crumbs and eggs to meat and mix all together.
Roll into logs (about the size of a baked potato).
Make 8 logs.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over logs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This can be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: raisin spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 11 1/2 x 17 1/2-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
In saucepan, add sugar, raisins, cinnamon, salt, water, butter or oleo and cloves. Boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Mix in sifted flour and baking soda, dissolved in water.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
While warm, cover with powdered sugar glaze.

title: cajun seafood casserole, texas style
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain on paper towel and when cool to touch, cut into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Set aside.

title: pudding surprise
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and light fruit cocktail and set aside.
Mix pudding with the buttermilk until thick.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Stir in the tidbits and fruit cocktail.
Put in covered dish and refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in a small bowl in microwave.
Combine sugars, eggs, flour, milk and vanilla, beating well.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, beating constantly.
Pour in pie shell and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 2 graham cracker pie crusts and freeze.

title: homemade blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together except pepper.
When smooth, add pepper.
A little or alot, whatever you like!

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix the yogurt and pudding together in a large bowl. Add the can of pineapple (do NOT drain it) to the yogurt/pudding mixture and stir. Fold the whipped topping (Cool Whip) to the mixture. Chill for 1 hour.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Take jello and add boiling water, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together and freeze.
Stir off and on until frozen.
Serve 2 scoops over 7-Up or Sprite.

title: corny rice
directions: In large skillet saute red pepper, onion, jalapeno and garlic in oil until tender. Add rice, corn, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until heated through. Sprinkle with green onion.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cook rice as package indicates. Combine broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup in a bowl.
Mix well. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs over top and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad casserole
directions: Brown meat in frying pan.
Drain off fat. Add refried beans, diced pepper, diced onion, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and chili powder to meat.
Mix thoroughly and continue heating until mixture begins to bubble.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix well. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice and raisin pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Beat in the eggs and slowly add your milk and vanilla.
Stir in the rice, raisins and butter.
Pour the mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in pudding.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions in Dutch oven.
Drain off fat. Stir beans and next 7 ingredients into beef mixture; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered 15 minutes stirring occasionally.
Ladle soup into bowls; top with desired toppings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches and butter until hot.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix equal amounts of flour, sugar and milk; stir well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake until golden brown in 400° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour in large 9 X 13 inch pan or dish.

title: dumplings
directions: Bring chicken broth to a slow simmer.
Add 1/2 stick butter. Roll small balls from biscuit dough.
Dip in flour and drop in simmering broth.
Add 1/2 stick butter.
Simmer about 30 or 40 minutes or until done.
Add chopped eggs and giblets.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in gallon jars.
Cover with vinegar. Let stand 6 weeks.
Pour off vinegar; slice cucumbers.
Put a layer of cucumbers and a layer of sugar until the jar is full, using about 4 1/2 pounds sugar.
Add 2 or 3 drops oil of cloves. Shake jars everyday until sugar has dissolved.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into sticks.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 4-5 hours.
Drain and pack into sterilized jars. Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes. Pour over cucumbers filling to 1/2 inch of the jar rim. Put caps on and screw band tightly.
Process for 5 mins.

title: peach cream cheese pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch glass pie dish.
Drain peaches; reserve juice.
Arrange peaches on batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon atop peaches.
Spread to within 1-inch of dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chili and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Combine chili, vegetable juice, mixed vegetables, taco sauce and onion.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 4 minutes.
Serve over rice and top with scoop of sour cream and grated cheese.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix butter, syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring well.
Stir in condensed milk; simmer, stirring constantly, until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over the popcorn.
Be sure all pieces are coated.
Rub a little butter on your hands and shape the balls.
Let them cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: ham and broccoli strata
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Toss broccoli, ham and cheese in a large bowl.
Spoon half of mixture in baking pan.
Arrange bread slightly overlapping on mixtures.
Pour remaining mixture over bread.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over dish.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Cream
margarine;
add
eggs
and bananas and mix well. Sift flour,
soda and sweetener twice.
Add to banana mixture and blend well.
Add nuts.
Turn batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch
loaf pan.
Bake
at 300° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together and put in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: green pepper relish (jelly)
directions: In a blender or food processor, chop one cup green peppers, a little red pepper and 1 cup vinegar.
Repeat this until the first three ingredients are blended well.
Add this mixture to the sugar and bring it to a fast boil.
(Watch closely because it boils over quickly.)
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add Certo and enough green food coloring to make a dark green (about the color of green pepper). Boil 1 minute more and seal in sterilized jars.
Serve over cream cheese, spread on Wheat Thins or favorite crackers.
Makes 12 1/2 pints (I got 7 pints).

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine the sugar, oil, egg, Egg Beaters or egg whites and bananas.
Add the flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 muffins.

title: pumpkin burgers
directions: Combine beef and onion; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes longer or until thickened.
Serve on buns.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar, milk, cocoa and vanilla. Bring to a boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal.
Stir in peanut butter.
Drop the mixture by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cookies set in refrigerator.

title: "hot" meat balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and roll into small (nickel size) balls. Bake in oven in edged pan for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Heat the enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour over drained meatballs in casserole dish.
Heat until ready to serve. Can be served with toothpicks.

title: fruit granola
directions: Heat first 3 in large heavy pan.
Stir.
Remove from heat and stir in next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Don't stir the first 15 minutes.
Then stir every 5 minutes until golden brown.
Cool, add fruit.
Store in tightly covered jar in the refrigerator or freeze.

title: chicken-nut pate
directions: Process nuts and chicken until finely ground.
Add mayonnaise, ginger, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar, blending well. Refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or mold and frost with sour cream.
Makes 3 cups.

title: shirley temple
directions: Fill highball or old fashion glass with ice cubes and ginger ale or 7-Up.
Add grenadine.
Garnish with orange slice and cherry.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare
Jell-O,
using
only 1 cup boiling water.
Add marshmallows
as
soon
as
the Jell-O is dissolved.
When the marshmallows
have
dissolved,
add
cranberry
sauce and cold water.
Blend and refrigerate.
When syrupy, take from refrigerator and add chopped celery, the diced apples and nuts. Mix well and return to refrigerator to set firm.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cover with cold water.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Cover vegetables with oil mixture.
Add drained pasta.
Mix all.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 325° until done.

title: one gallon bread and butter pickles
directions: Boil together.
Cool.
Pour over cucumber and onion slices. Refrigerate.
Turn everyday for 1 week.
They are wonderful!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain off the grease.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, mix corn meal, soda, salt, oil, milk, eggs and corn.
In an iron skillet, pour 1/2 corn meal mix batter. Put meat mixture on top, then sprinkle all the cheese.
Pour remaining corn meal batter on top.
You can sprinkle red peppers over the meat mixture if you like.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: greek omelette
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Pour into heated nonstick skillet and cook over medium heat.
Flip once, add chopped dried tomatoes, dried black olives, green onions and crumbled Feta cheese.
Serve with warm pita bread.

title: dill pickle dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and dill pickle juice.
Mix until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
(If creamier dip is desired, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.) Chill before serving. Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Pour glaze (recipe below) over hot cake.

title: icing for carrot cake
directions: Mix well and spread on cake.

title: st. james coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and spices together.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Reserve 1/2 cup of dry mixture. Combine milk and soda.
Add to remaining crumb mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and shortening together. Set aside 1 cup of mixture.
Add sour milk, baking soda and cinnamon. Sprinkle the 1 cup of sugar mixture on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Let cool.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Make 4 logs.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Slice straight from the freezer.
Each log makes 25 cookies.

title: saint nicholas cake
directions: Remove 2 tablespoons flour and mix with fruit and nuts. Combine remaining flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well to blend.
Add butter, milk and extract. Blend on low to mix, then 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in floured fruit and nut mixture.
Turn batter into greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost with glaze or icing sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll dough by teaspoonfuls into balls. Place onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Mash with a fork dipped in sugar with a crisscross pattern.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven until done, about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Make sure the Jell-O is evenly mixed throughout the salad.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer stuffing, chicken, mushrooms and pour soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: two-flavor fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, sugar, evaporated milk and butter or margarine.
Bring to a full boil over high heat, stirring frequently.
Boil 10 minutes or to 240° on a candy thermometer over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream or marshmallows, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips.
Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Blend in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: scotch bar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Spread on a jelly roll pan (with sides).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool 4 minutes.

title: banana pecan cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add bananas. Sift
together
flour,
baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately
with
buttermilk
to
which
vanilla has been added. Stir in pecans.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans and bake for 30 to
minutes
in
a
moderate
oven
(350°). Remove from pans and cool.
Spread whipped cream between layers and on top and sides of cake, or frost with 7 minute frosting.

title: herbed lima bean bake
directions: Cook lima beans as directed on package.
Cook onion in butter or oleo until soft.
Add stuffing mix and water.
Stir.
Set aside. Stir together sour cream or yogurt, flour and water.
Drain lima beans.
Add sour cream or yogurt mixture.
Stir.
Add 2/3 of stuffing mix and stir.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Combine cracker crumbs and the 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle evenly over corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: freezer bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients together and work in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast water; mix well.
Knead dough 20 to 30 times on lightly floured surface. Roll out and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bag.
Take out as needed and place on cookie sheet.
Place rolls in cold oven and turn oven on to 400°.
They will rise as oven heats.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add vegetables (cut up).
Add Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Stir.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to directions; let it become firm.
Crumble 1/3 of cake in bottom of a punch bowl.
In this order spoon 1/3 of pudding, 1/3 pie filling and 1/3 whipped cream.
Repeat this twice.
Spread whipped cream on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Twenty-four Hours Ahead:
Place brisket in heavy foil pouch or covered roasting pan.
Pour coffee over meat and seal, or cover with lid.
Bake at 200° for 24 hours.

title: eggplant and mushroom casserole
directions: Sprinkle eggplant with salt and let stand 20 minutes in water. Gently squeeze out salt water.
Dip each slice in beaten egg and fry quickly in oil just until egg sets.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Coat each breast with cooking spray; dredge in cereal mixture.
Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray and coat chicken again with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: applesauce cookieseverton, missouri
directions: Place raisins in boiling water and let sit for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Divide into pie shells.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cook sausage the night before for easy breakfast. Great with bacon, too.

title: peppermint pinwheels
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except food coloring.
Divide the dough evenly into halves; add food coloring to one half of dough, refrigerate for one hour.
Take the plain dough and roll on a lightly floured surface into a 16 by 9 inch rectangle.	Do the same with the color dough; then lay it over the plain dough.
Roll them and wrap tightly in wax paper. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
When finished heat oven to 400°; slice about 1/4 inch thick and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mincemeat
directions: Put the dried fruit, apples and almonds in a large bowl.
Add the sugar, suet, spices, lemon and orange rinds and juice and brandy or sherry, then mix all the ingredients together thoroughly. Cover the mincemeat and leave to stand for 2 days. Stir well.
Put into jars and cover.
Allow at least 2 weeks to mature before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Chop green pepper, cucumber and tomatoes fine.
Add to macaroni and add Miracle Whip to taste. Refrigerate until time to serve.
Stir before serving.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Prick chicken with tines of a fork.
In a small bowl, combine oil, lemon, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour over chicken and set aside 1 hour.

title: galabki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Remove core from cabbage with sharp knife.
Scald cabbage in boiling water.
Remove the leaves one by one as they wilt.
Set aside.
Mix meat with rice, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Fill each leaf with meat mixture, envelope style.
When rolled, tuck one end inward to hold together.
Line baking dish with sauerkraut.
Stand cabbage rolls on end on top of kraut.
Layer rest of kraut over rolls.
Mix tomato soup and tomato juice together and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until done.
Add a little water if necessary.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Serve with Triscuits or another sturdy cracker.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Cream 1 1/2 sticks butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour and half the cocoa.
Add and mix to creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with marshmallows.
Bake until marshmallows melt.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Sift powdered sugar and remaining cocoa.
Stir in remaining butter (melted) and vanilla.
Add milk to a spreading consistency.
Frost brownies.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: Fry sausage in skillet until brown and crumbly.
Combine sausage with rest of ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo or butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, but not completely done.
Drain.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix.
Mix milk and soup.
Layer in casserole in this order:
1/2 broccoli, 1/2 onions, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 soup mixture and 1/2 stuffing mixture. Repeat layer.
Do not cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen French-style green beans as package directs.
Pour into colander; drain, cool and squeeze out excess water.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; saute onions.
Add bacon, onions, ketchup and brown sugar to beans.
Mix.
Bake for 5 to 6 hours at 350° in covered pan.
Stir periodically.

title: jelly-roll cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick.
Gradually add sugar and lemon, then stir in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in flour, baking powder and salt (sifted together 5 times) alternately with cold water.
Line a shallow pan (cookie sheet) with well-greased waxed paper.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper, add corn, soups and sour cream.
Mix well and cook in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. The last 10 minutes, take out and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: cheesey green peppers
directions: Cut off tops from 8 green peppers or cut 4 in half lengthwise; remove seed and membrane.
Parboil 5 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain off excess fat.
Add corn, 1 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add 1 cup bread crumbs.
Yield:
approximately 4 1/2 cups.
Fill peppers with meat-corn mixture.
Combine 1/2 cup bread crumbs with butter. Top filled peppers with crumbs.
Pour remaining tomato sauce in bottom of baking pan; arrange peppers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, 25 or 30 minutes or until heated through.
Place half a cheese slice on each pepper.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: fruited cheesecake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and sugar.	Stir in butter or margarine until fully combined.
Press mixture onto bottom and
sides	of
a
9-inch
spring-form pan, firmly and evenly. Bake
for
8 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
(If using raisins, mix with rice before cooking, then cook rice as usual.)
Cook pudding according to directions.
Mix the two together and serve.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Spread rice in casserole.
Drain asparagus, reserving juice. Arrange asparagus spears on rice.
Mix mushroom soup and asparagus juice.
Pour over mixture and stir gently to moisten rice.
Place pork chops on top and season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients with your hands.
Dough will be tight. Make into balls; pat down a little.
They will spread some during baking.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and let cool and thicken slightly.
Mix cream cheese with milk.
Add Jell-O mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: summertime dip
directions: Combine in jar; shake well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with cold shrimp or raw vegetables.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine the cheese and milk in a saucepan; stir over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Add mixture and egg to muffin mix, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup noodles.
Combine ingredients.
Top with noodles.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°, uncovered.

title: french hot chocolate
directions: Place water and chocolate in 2 cup glass measure.
Microwave for about 2 minutes on High or until melted.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Microwave for about one minute, on High, or until hot. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate until served.
To make one serving, combine 3 tablespoons chocolate mixture and desired amount of milk in individual glass cups or mugs.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High or until hot.
About 1 cup of chocolate mixture makes about 5 (6-ounce) servings.
Chocolate mixture can be made ahead and refrigerated up to a week.

title: christmas trees
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream the shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg, flour, salt, baking powder and almond extract.
Add a few drops of green food coloring; mix well. Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets, using the tree plate.
Decorate with sugar or tiny candies.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mrs. bess' white fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in angel food cake pan (greased and floured). Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar. With blender or mixer, cut in butter until crumbly.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash to 1/2-inch thick.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: german chocolate squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler until melted. Combine cake mix, remaining milk and margarine. Beat with mixer until well combined, then add nuts. Press half mixture into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 6 minutes; sprinkle chocolate chips over top, then cover with caramel mixture. Crumble remaining cake mixture on top. Bake 17 to 20 minutes. Cool for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spread dried beef over bottom of pan (greased Pyrex dish). Wrap a strip of bacon around each breast and secure with a toothpick.
Lay each breast on piece of dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together; pour mixture over the top.
It should cover the chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Uncover and cook 1 1/2 hours more at 275° (total 3 hours).

title: chicken nut casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons flour, the chicken broth, salt, pepper and milk in
a large skillet.
Add the chicken and mushroom gravy.
Mix and place in casserole.
Put cashew nuts and chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: asparagus au jus
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Mix 1 cup au jus gravy according to package directions.
Pull aside onion and mushrooms.
Pour au jus liquid into skillet; add asparagus shoots.
Simmer until tender.
Add onion and mushrooms back to skillet.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble half of cake into bottom of bowl and arrange layers as follows:
half of pudding mix, 1 can cherry pie filling, 1/2 can pineapple, 1/2 container Cool Whip and 1/2 cup nuts.
Follow with remainder of cake and other ingredients.

title: broccoli bread or muffin
directions: Mix and cook in muffin pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into greased baking dish or pan.
Dot with margarine.
Bake until firm in 375° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Combine in 9-inch skillet chicken, stock, carrots and peas. Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti and tarragon.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove lid and cook 5 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets.
Keep 1/2 cup liquid; combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix with beet liquid, vinegar and margarine.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add beets and heat well.
Let set a few minutes.
Serves 5.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter; mix with flour and pour milk on gradually.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add corn, seasoning, yolks of eggs (well beaten) and stiffly beaten whites.
Turn into buttered baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: In a saucepan, blend together butter or margarine, flour, salt and cheeses.
Add milk all at once; cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: skinless oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove skin from chicken.
Place chicken in skim milk.
Shake off excess and roll in crumbs. Place chicken in an oiled pan.
Bake 45 minutes until crispy.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Add oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Slowly add buttermilk, fig preserves, nuts and vanilla. Stir.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Fill 3/4 full.
You may need to use 2 pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate or coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Place over medium heat and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and cocoa when thick.
If making coconut, add coconut now and pour in pie shell. If making coconut, leave out cocoa.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup to onion and celery; bring to a boil.
Mix the onions with rice and broccoli; put in casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: date balls
directions: Cook over low heat 10 minutes the dates, sugar and eggs. Remove from heat and add 2 cups Rice Krispies and 1 cup nuts, finely chopped.
Cool on wax paper.
Roll into balls and roll in flaked coconut or 4x sugar.
Makes about 100.

title: fruit juice shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend 30 seconds on high speed.
Serve all at once.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for 3/4 to 1 hour or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: italian rice balls
directions: Add pepper and parsley to rice; let cool.
Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Cook in oil until golden brown (drain on paper towel).
May need flour on your hands when rolling into balls, sometimes sticky.
Before serving, bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Make into rolls.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until browned.
(Makes 1 loaf of bread.)

title: meat loaf(from recipes for diabetics)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into a loaf. Place in foil-lined 5 x 9-inch pan.
Bake until done, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch) and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into boiling water in medium saucepan.
Add shortening and enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Form into small 1/2-inch thick cakes.
Fry on hot greased griddle.
Turn when brown on bottom.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and granulated sugar until lumps are removed.
In bottom of graham cracker crust, slice banana in thin round slices and evenly cover bottom of crust.
Pour the prepared mixture on top of the prepared banana crust and refrigerate until the mixture is firm (approximately 2 hours).
Mix strawberries with 1/2 cup of granulated sugar.
Pour over the chilled pie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Grease 2 loaf pans*.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine Aioli, yogurt and oregano.
Add to chicken mixture. Toss to coat. Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, except the granulated sugar; mix well.
Add the carrot mixture to the flour mixture, stirring until moistened.
Line 24 muffin cups with paper baking cups; spoon mixture into muffin cups.
Sprinkle tops with granulated sugar.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Serve with butter, margarine or cream cheese. Yields 24 medium size muffins.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil potatoes and salt until done; drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: velvety chocolate pie
directions: Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Mix the dry ingredients together and add to the scalded milk.
Stir until blended and cook, stirring often, until mixture begins to thicken. Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir and cool slightly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place sugar in small saucepan.
Combine cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water, stirring until smooth.
Add to saucepan along with 3/4 cup water.
Cook over medium-low heat until thickened, stirring frequently.
Add jello; stir to dissolve.
Line pie shell with strawberries, stem end down, filling in where necessary with smaller berries.
Pour sauce over top.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Put in bottom of pam sprayed baking dish.
Add soup with 1 1/2 c. water.
Mix stove top stuffing as directed on box.
Put dressing on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese on top of dressing.
Bake until it bubbles.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Combine apples, sweetened condensed milk and cinnamon; set aside.
Cut 1/2 cup oleo in 1 cup biscuit mix until crumbly. Stir in apple mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar. Cut in rest of oleo until crumbly; add nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake for 1 hour until golden.
Serve with ice cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable christmas tree
directions: Cut all vegetables into chunks.
Place wooden picks in cut vegetables.
Arrange in cone from bottom up.
Arrange remainder of vegetables around base in plate.
Serve with low-calorie dip.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened milk and water.
Add pudding and mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup mixture in 2 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Top 1/3 each with wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat, ending with pudding.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in muffin tins on 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add a little jam and you'll be licking your fingers.

title: crustless cheesecake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl of electric mixer and beat at medium speed 20 minutes or until light and creamy.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, put Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding, stir until mixed well.
Add marshmallows, if desired.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix and serve. Make only what you are going to use; do not save.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar. Blend well. Add dry ingredients, stir in vanilla, apples and nuts. Put in greased tube pan or 9 x 13 dish. Bake 350° for 50 or 60 minutes. Poke fork holes in cake while hot. Pour topping over hot cake.

title: beef barley vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add all other ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Put in a mixing bowl the lukewarm milk, yeast, salt and flour. Beat thoroughly. Cover and let rise 1/2 hour. Add melted butter or salad oil, light brown sugar, eggs, nutmeg and flour. Beat well. Cover and let rise again until dough is light. Punch down. Add more flour if the dough is too soft to handle.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine wafers and melted margarine; press onto bottom and sides (halfway up) 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, softened margarine and eggs; beat on high speed 15 minutes.
Do not underbeat!
Spread sugar mixture on top of crust.
Top with bananas.
Cover with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over fruit and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: chili beans
directions: Chop onions and pepper; brown in oil.
Add meat; brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for at least 15 minutes (longer, if you have time).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: candy apples
directions: Mix sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil and cook until it reaches 300° on a candy thermometer.
Do not stir while cooking.
Add food coloring last.
Keep fire low while dipping apples.
Lay on a cookie sheet.
Spread with Pam.
Makes 12 to 15 medium apples.
Make sure apples are washed and dried good.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar. Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until creamy. Add flour to creamed mixture with milk and extracts.
Mix until just blended well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
(Cake will rise above pan and settle back down on cooling.)
Cool in pan 15 minutes on rack before removing to rack.

title: caramel coffee rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Put frozen rolls in pan, about 15; sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Combine butter, sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Cook until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Cover tightly and let set overnight on the counter. Bake in the morning at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and turn upside down on wax paper while still hot.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Cut margarine into flour until crumbs form. Add milk to flour mixture and drizzle over chicken.
Bake at 350° to 375° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: asparagus and chicken casserole
directions: Shake Accent on chicken breasts.
Saute in oil about 8 minutes and drain on paper towels.
Drain asparagus (frozen or canned) and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken strips over asparagus. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over the top. Sprinkle cheese; cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french fried onions
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onions.
Peel and slice the onions and soak in cold water.
Dry and separate into rings.
Dip in batter and deep fry until done (390° to 400°).
Drain on paper towels.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Add margarine to hot potatoes.
Add margarine, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir together.
Add cinnamon, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and nuts.
Mix together well.
Place in a greased 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Pour into greased baking dish and sprinkle with the following topping.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first four items in microwave bowl.
Cook 9 minutes on High.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy.
Pour onto greased baking sheet.
Cool 15 minutes or longer.
Break into pieces.

title: busy day cake
directions: Makes 2 round layers (1-inch thick) or an 8-inch square cake (1 1/2-inches thick).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: belgium cookies(gouflets)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set for half an hour.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles.
Return drained noodles to kettle; stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
If desired, sprinkle paprika over bread crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into cold pie shell and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: bob haskell's smoked turkey
directions: You will need a charcoal pan heaping full and water pan full.

title: carol's carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sherry's snowflake salad
directions: Using electric mixer, whip both packages of Dream Whip according to package directions increasing milk by one cup.
(Be sure to check date on package to make sure the Dream Whip is fresh.)
Add cream cheese (regular or lite) and sugar.
Fold in fruit cocktail, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into large oblong Pyrex dish.
To add color, decorate top with red cherries, drained mandarin oranges, nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix cracker crumbs in 1/4 pound butter.
Add clams, garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix and stuff shrimp.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Baste a few times with sherry and 2 tablespoons butter.
The tails will curl up when done.

title: chocolate date cookies(rich's cookies)
directions: Grease well a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Mix dates, sugar and butter with 1/2 cup water in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Beat in eggs.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, soda and salt together and add alternately with milk. Add bananas.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: karen's creative beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, sour cream, mushroom soup, chicken soup, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Bring to a simmer; stir in flour, if desired.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chopped onions or chives on top.
Good when served over hot rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Divide evenly and pour into pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is done.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: About 10 minutes before serving or a day ahead, in a small bowl, combine mustard, honey and soy sauce until blended.
Serve over slices of baked ham or other meats and pour about 1 tablespoon over each slice.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Sift flour and salt together.
Combine flour mixture with creamed mixture.
Leave dough in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Roll out dough.
Make small triangles in dough with knife or fancy pie cutter.
Place preserves (about 1/4 teaspoon) in center of each triangle.
Lift 3 points of triangle; fold and pinch together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and

make a layer of 1/2 of each ingredient, then make another layer with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or microwave approximately 15 minutes at normal setting, turning dish when half done.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper in 3 tablespoons of oil until onions are yellow.
Cook hamburger until it falls apart and is gray in color.

title: microwaved shrimp scampi
directions: Cut up the margarine and put in casserole dish for melting (1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes) in microwave; don't burn it! Remove.
Stir in all the ingredients, except the shrimp.
Add the shrimp, tossing until evenly coated.
Cover the dish.
Put back into the microwave.
Cook until the shrimp is cooked (4 to 7 minutes), stirring twice during this time.
Remove.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with linguine or whatever you have in mind.

title: marinated olives(international)
directions: Spread olives between layers of paper towels and blot dry to remove most of the brine. Mix together the olives, dried herbs and orange zest in a bowl. Loosely pack into a glass jar; lay the herb sprigs on top and add olive oil to cover. Cover tightly and store for 2 days to 1 week.

title: california casserole
directions: Pour bags of veggies in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish; add in spices, cubed butter and cubed Velveeta. Mix evenly. Pour Ritz crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for 30 minutes of time. Then remove foil. Stir. Wait 15 minutes; stir again. Bake 15 more minutes, uncovered. The most delicious way to get your green leafy veggies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 3 ingredients; add sifted dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Cool well before removing from pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Flatten with the tines of a fork.
