Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter; saute celery, onions and bell pepper.
Add flour; stir until dissolved.
Add tomatoes, green onion tops, parsley, finely chopped garlic and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer a while, then add seasoned shrimp and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Jalapenos may be added, if desired.
If more gravy is needed, add a little cornstarch and water.
Serve over rice.

title: friendship cake and starter
directions: You will need a large gallon jar.
In the jar, combine pineapple, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons brandy.
Let sit in jar for 2 weeks, stirring daily.
At the end of 2 weeks, add maraschino cherries, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of brandy.
Let sit for 2 more weeks, stirring daily.
During the fourth week, add the canned peaches, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons brandy.
Let stand another 2 weeks, stirring daily.
Separate the liquid from the fruit.
The liquid is the starter.
Use the fruit on ice cream or cake.
Do not refrigerate the liquid.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet until it loses its redness. Remove from skillet and cook macaroni, onion and green pepper in meat fat until macaroni is yellow.
Add meat back to skillet along with tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked. Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water; stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until completely thawed.
Add nuts, pineapple and bananas (optional). Stir completely.
Pour in small glass pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Top with Cool Whip and Serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Remove and add flour.
Use a heavy pot and brown flour to a dark roux.
Add onions, parsley and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add water, rice, seasonings and browned meat.
When it comes to a boil, lower heat to lowest point and cook for about 1 hour covered tightly.
When rice is done, remove lid and let cook for a few minutes until rice dries a little.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Press lightly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes to form coarse crumbs. Cool. Divide crumb mixture in half. Press half into the same baking pan.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine onions and butter in 3-quart casserole.
Cover; microwave at High 6 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes, or until onions are soft and translucent.
Pour chicken and beef broth into bowl.
Add water to make 1 quart.
Stir in onions.
Cover; microwave 4 to 6 minutes, until heated through.

title: buster sundae pie
directions: Layer 2 cups of vanilla ice cream into a cooled pie crust. Drizzle with 1/4 cup caramel and 1/4 cup fudge toppings.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Layer remaining 2 cups of ice cream over peanuts. Drizzle with remaining caramel and fudge toppings.
Freeze several hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and cherries.

title: betty's peach cobbler
directions: Lightly spray casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) with vegetable oil spray.
Cut peaches into small pieces and fill bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the peaches.
Sprinkle lightly with water until damp.
Cook at 350° until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: cranberry apple nut salad
directions: Boil the water, then mix Jell-O. Dissolve completely. Add apples, celery, nuts and marshmallows.

title: old fashioned seven layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together. Add eggs. Cream that and add buttermilk, flour and vanilla. Beat together. Cook in 6 or 7 layers at 350° until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Quarter artichokes and slice water chestnuts.
Add green beans.
Mix Green Goddess dressing and onion soup mix.
Mix together gently and refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter or shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt (optional) and sour cream.
Mix until all ingredients are blended and dough is in a ball form.

title: old-fashion rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Bring water to boil. Stir in rice and salt. Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 30 minutes. Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes. Combine eggs, sugar, and vanilla in bowl. Gradually stir in rice mixture; mix well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. If desired, stir in raisins and sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon over top. Place casserole in a pan containing about 1 inch hot water. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve warm or chilled. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla to starter in bowl, mix well and add remaining ingredients (except nuts).
Stir well and add nuts.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans, well-greased, or 3 small loaf pans.
Sprinkle extra cinnamon and sugar on the top of each loaf before baking, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange julius surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple bran bread
directions: Measure pineapple syrup and add water if necessary to make 2/3 cup.
Pour over bran and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add walnuts, crushed pineapple, egg and melted shortening to bran mixture and add to sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until just blended.
Turn into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: artichoke and green bean casserole
directions: Cut artichokes in half and combine in casserole dish with green beans.
Mix olive oil and artichoke liquid; fold into artichokes.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs together and add to casserole.
Mix well.
Top with more crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or enough to heat thoroughly.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix milk and soup together; stir in beaten eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Knife comes out clean when inserted in middle indicating it is done.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet or chill until firm enough to handle and shape small amounts of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: phillip's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Mix soda, flour,
sugar
and buttermilk.
Bring to boil oleo, vegetable oil,
water
and	cocoa
powder.	Mix together with soda mixture.
Bake in
13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, egg, milk, onion and seasonings.
Form into balls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter, using as little pressure as possible.
Brown well in drippings.
Place meatballs in heavy skillet.
Add water.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes on low heat.

title: mint lemonade
directions: Mix limeade.
Combine mint leaves and confectioners sugar; crush with a fork.
Add to limeade; cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
Strain.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut in shortening with dry ingredients.
Beat egg, water and vinegar; mix with ingredients.
Divide into 4 or 5 balls.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Mix and add fruit. Gently fold in
Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and pepper.
Wash okra; cut into 1/2-inch slices. Dredge in corn meal mixture.
Okra should be moist for meal mixture to coat well.
Lightly coat a
15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
Spread okra in a single layer. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crisp; stir occasionally.
Contains less than 1 gram fat.

title: pineapple whip ice cream
directions: Mix well in order given.
Can use other fruit if desired instead of the pineapple.
Freeze in the ice cream freezer. Makes about a gallon.

title: peanut butter round-up
directions: Beat shortening and brown sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Shape dough to form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Press crisscrosses on each cookie with fork.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Cook lentils until soft and rather dry.
Mix in egg, garlic powder, milk, cereal and onion that was sauteed in oil.
Put into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Mash bananas in blender. Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Add 7-Up to form a slush.

title: new orleans chicken creole
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until tender.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix milk and flour.
Add water to milk and flour. Add milk mixture to tomato; stir constantly until thick.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cook until hot; stir in cheese.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all into loaf in a baking dish.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 4 layers.
Take whipped topping, sour cream and confectioners sugar and mix well; beat until thick and holds its shape like meringue (about 12 or 15 minutes at high speed).
Wash, clean and slice strawberries. Stack cake using lots of filling and 1/3 of berries on each layer. Cover the top and sides with the remaining topping mix.
Keep refrigerated.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Pour milk over Grape-Nuts; cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add egg and shortening to Grape-Nuts mixture; stir well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only enough to dampen all flour.
Turn into greased loaf pan; let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes one 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf.

title: potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and brush the potatoes; slice into wedges.
Place in a microwave dish with a small amount of water until partially cooked.
Mix the seasonings into the flour.
Mix the egg with the milk.
Dip potatoes into milk; dust with seasoned flour.
Place on a pastry sheet.
Drizzle with oil or spray with Pam.
Bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown and tender. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: supreme sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips) until smooth and creamy.
Fold in chips.
Put into a well-greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove; let cool. Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip.

title: easy homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients; mix well and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: buffalo bills onion
directions: Cut 12 (12-inch) squares of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Place an onion, cut side up, in center of each.
Dot each onion with margarine; sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Wrap well; place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired (onions can also be grilled).

title: quick beans 'n rice
directions: Wash beans under clear water to remove original liquid.
(This will greatly reduce sodium.)
Add beans to water and black pepper in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a brisk boil.
Add rice; stir. Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes for liquid to absorb.
Stir and serve.
For extra "zip," sprinkle with crushed red pepper or your favorite spice.
(Black and red pepper are 2 of my favorites.) Makes 2 servings.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix all ingredients into a gallon jar.
Add enough cold water to fill gallon jar.
Stir well until dissolved.

title: mom's homemade pot pie
directions: Use just enough flour to roll out after all mixed together. Cook for 20 minutes or longer until tender.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix honey, pineapple juice concentrate, vanilla, 2 unbeaten egg whites, pineapple and carrot puree.
Stir into flour mixture and mix until just blended.
Stir in raisins.
Gently stir in 2 lightly beaten egg whites.
Do not overmix.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and place the ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix an additional 1/2 stick butter, melted, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and 2 1/2 cups of cornflakes.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown meat and pour off excess fat.
Add all ingredients except the rice.
Cook slowly, covered, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir in rice; heat through and serve.
Serves 6.

title: sand tarts(everyone's favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients well using a wooden spoon. Pinch off small pieces of dough (teaspoon size) and roll to thickness of pencil. Form into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll immediately in powdered sugar.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and add flour over medium heat.
Add milk and chicken broth and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Add broccoli that has been steamed in 1/2 cup water.
Add salt last.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chevron rice bake
directions: Reserve the sliced luncheon meat for top.
Combine cubed meat, cooked rice, peas, eggs, soup, milk, parsley, onion, curry powder and pepper.
Spread in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch metal baking pans. Drain the peaches; stud peaches with a few whole cloves.
Arrange peaches and meat slices atop rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until heated through.
Makes 24 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: fresh cherry cobbler
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in cherries and almond extract. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
When starts to boil, time for 1 minute.
Pour ingredients from saucepan into ungreased cake pan (keep cherry mixture hot in oven).

title: marion's version of tropical dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump and spread in order listed, the cherries, undrained pineapple, dry cake mix and nuts.
Do not mix, but smooth each layer as you spread it. Pour melted margarine evenly over the top layer. Sprinkle and spread coconut on top. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done.
Serves 12.

title: mu's jam cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into three 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Combine shortening, eggs, sugar and bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix with banana mixture.
Add nuts, chips and cherries. Pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 350°.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put chicken in stock pot.
Place quartered onions, carrots, celery and bay leaf on top.
Cover chicken with water.
Bring to boil and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Remove chicken from pot.
Let cool.
Strain broth from vegetables. take meat from bone. Set aside. put broth back into stock pot.
Bring to boil. place noodles in broth.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add chopped onion and celery during last 5 minutes.
Place chicken back into broth.
Heat through.
If it needs to be thickened, add some cornstarch mixed with water.
Serve over mashed potatoes.
This is a family favorite.

title: granny's apple crisp
directions: Toss sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Put in 5 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put apples and cranberries through food chopper after apples are cored and pared.
Clean oranges and lemon; put through food chopper.
Add sugar and blend.
Chill a few hours and serve.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add sour milk, oil and eggs to dry ingredients and store in refrigerator in an airtight container.
This may be stored in the refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pleasing potato pizza
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil; cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until very tender.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter, set aside and keep warm. Cream 1 stick butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda and buttermilk.
Then add candy bar mixture to ingredients, add nuts. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: spinach spread
directions: Wash and drain spinach; place on paper towels. Press until spinach is barely moist.
Combine spinach and cream cheese; mix well, stirring in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-cup baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Spread on crackers or party rye bread. Yield: 2 cups.

title: simply cube steak
directions: Lightly brown cube steak in olive oil on both sides. Sprinkle cube steak with the dry onion soup mix.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over cube steak with dry onion soup.
Cover and simmer 45 minute to 1 hour.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pear liquid to a boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool at room temperature until syrupy.
Meanwhile, puree pears in a blender.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and lemon juice until fluffy and smooth. Add pureed pears and mix well.
Prepare whipped topping according to package directions; fold into pear mixture.
Fold in cooled gelatin.
Pour into an oiled 4 1/2 cup mold.
Chill overnight. Just before serving, unmold onto a lettuce lined platter.
Garnish with pear halves and mint leaves.

title: in-a-hurry chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add Manwich and chili powder; mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add corn, butter, salt and milk. Stir
thoroughly.
Pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 3/4 cup milk.
Stir in nuts, cherries and chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Make frosting and spread while still warm.

title: refrigerator pickle cuke salad
directions: Wash cucumbers but do not peel; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In a large bowl, combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle in salt and dill.
Stir well.
Let stand, uncovered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican half moons
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press each biscuit and flatten. Spoon cheese mixture over half of flattened biscuit.
Fold empty biscuit half over cheese mixture.
Press seam of "half moon" with a fork to seal.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serve and enjoy!

title: barbecue beef
directions: Remove as much fat as possible from beef.
Place in roast pan. Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over roast.
Roast at 325° for 4 hours or until you can easily shred with fork.
Serve on Italian or kaiser rolls.
Can easily be doubled or tripled. Freezes well.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: In small bowl combine garlic powder, ginger and pepper.
Blend well.
Sprinkle mixture on both sides of meat.
Save mixture. Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add meat; cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
In small bowl add to the saved mixture the chili sauce, soy sauce and honey.
Pour over meat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix liquids; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts, raisins and dates and mix.
Spray four 1-pound coffee cans with Pam.
Divide batter into cans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool; remove from cans. Wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: mini reubens
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Spread butter and mustard on bread.
Put corned beef and 1 teaspoon sauerkraut on top, then slice of cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted.
Can be cut in half.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix up confectioners sugar as directed on confectioners sugar wrapper.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Frost on chocolate cake.
Serve.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon extract and blend. Sift dry ingredients together and combine with raisins and pecans.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: easy crescent dogs
directions: Split hot dogs within 1/2 inch of ends, cut down 3/4 of the way down.
Cut cheese into thirds and place strips in each slit. Wrap 1 crescent dough triangle around each hot dog.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up at 375 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Knead with hands until it looks like pie dough.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in granulated sugar; press into mold.
Pop out on waxed paper.
Mints may be frozen in a covered container.
(Add color with food coloring, if desired.) Makes 200 mints.

title: spicy shrimp and noodle soup
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Peel and devein shrimp.
In medium mixing bowl, combine lemon juice, chili powder, cumin and pepper; add shrimp.
Toss to coat.
Let shrimp stand for 20 minutes at room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile in large saucepan, bring water to boiling.
Stir in 1 noodle flavor packet (reserve remaining flavor packet for another use) and the broken noodles. Return to boiling and cook 1 minute.
Add shrimp and cook for 1 to 2 minutes more or until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in salsa, beans, corn, snipped cilantro and green onion.
Heat through.
To serve, top each serving with cheese and garnish with cilantro, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 main dish servings.

title: fettucini alfredo cream sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Add 1/2 to 1 package dry Italian (Good Seasons) dressing mix.
This will cover 1 pound of fettucini pasta.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Blend oregano into spaghetti sauce.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese, and sauce alternately in a 6x10 baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Stir to blend. Use as marinade for steaks, roasts or chicken.
Marinate for 1 hour at room temperature in covered container or in refrigerator overnight, turning meat occasionally.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in big bowl.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and egg with broccoli. Put into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Crush crackers and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at
350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: surprise pie
directions: Prepare beans in usual manner with regular seasonings and bacon. (Or use left-overs).
Mash very well and measure exactly.
Mix with sugar, eggs, butter, and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 400° until firm.
Garnish with pecans, if desired.
Tastes like a pecan pie.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add onion.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of a pie plate.
Top with grated cheese. Combine milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over beef and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and chill. Delicious fruit salad for special occasions. Will keep in the refrigerator 3 or 4 days.

title: double apple salad
directions: Combine apples; let set in pineapple juice.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover salad and chill.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt and combine chocolate squares and butter.
Add milk slowly to chocolate and butter mixture.
Add slowly sugar, cook in a heavy pan.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add a little salt and vanilla.

title: microwave chicken breasts
directions: Spread mustard
on
both
sides of chicken and sprinkle with pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Melt butter in a glass
measuring cup and then stir in lemon juice, garlic salt and tarragon.
Place chicken on a microwave roasting rack and brush with
butter
sauce
and
microwave
on High for 10 minutes. Rearrange
chicken
without
turning so the uncooked portions are on the outside of dish.
Again brush with butter sauce on High for
to 15 minutes or until chicken is done brushing with butter sauce every 5 minutes.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape meat mixture into loaf.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Drizzle top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Mix well.
Fill hamburg or wiener buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake in a slow 250° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator.
Good to eat with crackers.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all in one bowl by hand.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350°.
Use whatever frosting you desire.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Beat egg white with water in mixer bowl until frothy.
Stir in pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Add to pecans; mix well.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Place in decorative airtight containers.
Makes 1 pound.

title: cheesy meatball sandwiches
directions: Step 1:
Place frozen meatballs in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: banana pudding cream filling
directions: Microwave milk on High for 3 to 5 minutes or to boiling.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and egg together.
Add about 1/2 cup of hot milk, stirring to blend.
Add to remaining milk and cook for 4 to 5 minutes on 70% power or until thickened.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Cool.

title: walnut swiss cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients except walnuts and crackers in medium bowl until creamy.
Stir in walnuts.
Pack into 2-cup crock or non-metal container; cover tightly, no longer than 2 weeks. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with walnuts if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rotel dip
directions: Slice cheese and melt.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Butter toast heavily on both sides and cut into pieces.
In a 9 x 9-inch glass pan (greased), put toast pieces first, then cheese and then sausage.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter; mix with cake mix.
Place pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle mixture of cake and butter over the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: In small bowl, beat egg with garlic powder, parsley and green onion.

title: betsy's chocolate cream dessert
directions: Mix the first 4
ingredients
together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick garlic sticks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: classic dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Gradually add milk, water and butter to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour, beat 2 minutes at higher speed, scraping bowl occasionally. With spoon stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Cover tightly and let set 2 to 4 hours.
Punch dough down, turn out on lightly floured board.
Shape any way you wish and place on pan.
Cover, let rise to double in bulk, about 40 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter and granola logs
directions: Stir together peanut butter and honey in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in raisins, then the granola, until blended.
Form 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture into 2 x 3/4-inch logs.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour until firm.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Beat sugar, egg white and cold water to a peak in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, baking powder and marshmallows.
Whip and put on cake.
Reserve some; add food coloring and swirl on cake.

title: lovely lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or pie plate lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle bottom with cracker crumbs. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container. Add cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Cover and blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan; smooth top.
Chill until set; about 4 hours.
When ready to serve; remove side of pan.
Top cheesecake with pie filling.
Serves 8.

title: hawaiian delight(lisa's favorite)
directions: Roll out cookies (save out 1/3 cup) and mix with 1/4 pound butter.
Press into pan and bake at 325° for 10 or 15 minutes. Cool.

title: flintstone special
directions: Put 1 cup noodles in casserole.
Next, hamburger, salt, pepper, then tomatoes over hamburger, then rest of noodles.
Top with grated cheese, the more cheese, the better.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Run persimmons through colander with milk.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Sift dry ingredients plus spices and add slowly to liquid. Add butter. Pour into large pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: brown sugar seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar until hard ball forms in water.
Pour syrup over stiffly beaten egg whites, gradually beating constantly until creamy.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: mother's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Sift together next 5 ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix boiling water and soda.
Add to sugar mixture, alternating with flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Ice with caramel icing.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add flour.
Add chopped nuts, salt, cocoa and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread marshmallow cream on top while hot.
Let cool 1 hour.

title: mock boursin
directions: Blend all the ingredients together and pat into a flat, round mold between
waxed paper.	Sprinkle the lemon pepper on all sides.
Refrigerate.
Make	day
before.
Time of preparation:
10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grilled garlic tenderloin
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well. Place tenderloins in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish; brush olive oil mixture over all sides of tenderloins. Cover and chill 3 hours. Grill tenderloins, covered, over hot coals 12 to 15 minutes or until meat thermometer reads 160°, turning once. Cut into slices to serve.

title: bubble fun
directions: Mix water, dish liquid and glycerine in container.
Shape bubble wand out of florist wire.
Have fun!

title: blueberry pie with bananas
directions: Mix milk, juice and Cool Whip.
Fold in berries.
Be careful not to crush.
Cut bananas crossways and put in bottom of shells. Pour in fruit mixture.
Chill.

title: ma's nothing stuffing
directions: Dice onions and celery.
Add spices to cup of boiling water. Simmer until soft.
Tear light whole wheat bread into pieces. Combine everything.
If mix is too dry, add more skim milk.
Bake in oven next to your turkey or chicken for 20 minutes.
Stuffing inside a bird adds fat from the meat and skin.
This stuffing is so tasty.
Serves 8.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients, then apples.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, syrup, oil and salt. Add flour gradually, making dough just stiff enough to handle easily.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Shape into loaves and let rise again, until double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° for 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and remove from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes; set skins aside.
Bring pulp to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Press pulp through sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins to pulp.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add lemon juice, butter or margarine and grape pulp. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle Crumb Topping over filling.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 40 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and flour together.
Put sausage mixture in deep dish pie crust.
Combine beaten eggs with parsley flakes, evaporated milk and onion salt.
Pour egg mixture over it.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse with cold water.
Add vegetables and toss mixture with dressing and seasoning.
Salt to taste.

title: crunchy turkey casserole
directions: Mix turkey, celery, almonds, onions, mayonnaise and soup together.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat olive oil or butter in frying pan.
Add hamburger meat and brown.
Add cabbage chopped in long strips and cooked until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square pan.
Mix dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients, including melted butter.
Mix thoroughly. Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot pastry cookies
directions: Combine flour and salt; set aside.
Cream butter or margarine and warm cheese.
Stir in flour mixture by hand just until blended.
Divide dough into fourths, wrap in plastic wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 400° and lightly grease baking sheets.
Combine apricot preserves, coconut and walnuts; set aside.
Working with one fourth of dough at a time, roll on floured pastry cloth or other floured surface into 8 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut rolled dough into 2-inch squares. Spread each square with 1 teaspoon apricot mixture leaving edges of dough uncovered.
Moisten one corner of dough with water. Beginning at opposite corner roll toward moistened corner and press lightly to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Makes 80.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Drain all juices and save;
mix instant vanilla pudding mix with
juice.
Will	be
thin;
pour over fruit.
Will last several days in refrigerator.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix and let stand for 2 days in refrigerator.
Take one cup out and feed it.
Use other cup for bread.
Let cup that you feed stay out of refrigerator for one day.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together Open Pit barbecue sauce and brown sugar gradually, mixing constantly to avoid lumping together.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before using.

title: old fashion goulash
directions: Flour beef cuts and
brown
in	oil.
Salt
and pepper. Cover with water.
Add
pinch
of red pepper, onion, allspice, cloves and
bay
leaf.
Simmer for several hours until meat is tender. Add catsup and gingersnaps.
Cook for 1/2 hour longer and serve.

title: pad thai
directions: In a large bowl, combine the noodles with water to cover. Soak until just tender about 45 minutes, then drain.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large, microwave-safe bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes or until heated. Stir every 2 minutes.
Serve over your favorite pasta. Makes about 3 cups.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers and place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except coconut and mix until blended.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Make several days ahead to allow flavors to blend.

title: alberta's mushroom soup
directions: Chop mushrooms, stock, onions and lemon juice.
Boil.
In another pan melt butter and add flour on high heat.
Add lite cream and then heavy cream, salt and pepper to make a smooth sauce.
Mix all together and add sherry.
Garnish with parsley.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add eggs, mixing well.

Add melted margarine and chocolate, mixing only until blended and smooth. Gradually add milk, mixing and keeping bowl scraped down well. Stir in vanilla (more if desired) and salt. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of coconut over bottom of two 10-inch unbaked pie shells.
Pour chocolate mixture into shells and bake approximately 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Thaw pastry sheets about 20 minutes. Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Saute in butter about 1 minute on each side.
Drain, set aside to cool.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Pour all ingredients into a bowl and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple betty cake
directions: Mix margarine, yellow cake mix and coconut.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the can of apple pie filling over the mixture pressed in the pan.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle it over the apple pie filling.
Beat egg, then mix it with the sour cream and spread it over the sugar and cinnamon. Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: hot dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and heat 15 minutes.
You may add chopped nutmeats.

title: scalloped potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: killer bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan and garlic in large bowl to blend. Arrange bread, cut side up, on a large cookie sheet. Butter bread. Broil until crisp and brown.
Spread Parmesan mixture over cut sides of bread.
Broil until top is puffed and golden brown. Sprinkle with chopped basil.
Cut bread into wedges and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add squash and pineapple. Add dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes on rack before turning out.

title: italian sauced fish
directions: Arrange fillets in single layer on well greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt. Mix spaghetti sauce and onion, pour over fillets. Bake uncovered at 350° till fish flakes easily with a fork, about 25-30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven till cheese melts, about 3 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 6 tablespoons margarine.
Place in bottom of pan.
Beat until thick 1/4 pound margarine, vanilla, egg and powdered sugar.
Spoon onto crust.
Cut bananas into slices and place on top of filling.
Put crushed pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this.
Sprinkle with cherries and nuts.

title: pot-roasted pork
directions: Rub pork roast with salt and pepper.
Make tiny slits in meat and insert slivers of garlic.
Place roast in broiler pan; broil for 15 to 20 minutes to remove excess fat.
Put 1 sliced onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Add browned pork roast, remaining onion and other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 10 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove meat to platter; thicken gravy, if desired.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together with hand beater or mixer; add remaining ingredients.
Mix until very smooth.
Spray a spring-form pan with "Pam" or nonsticking spray; pour batter in pan and place in pan of water (water should come up at least halfway on the outside of pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; turn off oven and leave in oven 1/2 hour longer.
Remove from oven and cool on wire rack.
Chill approximately 8 hours. Remove from pan before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: *To
test,
put pinch of sugar on top.	Wait 5 minutes. Should be foam on top, if good.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then peel and slice.
Pour salt, oil and vinegar or French dressing over warm potatoes.
Let cool. To cooled potato mixture, add pepper, celery seed, chopped onions, sliced eggs, bacon and olives.
Then add gently the mayonnaise. Serves about 18.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Combine pimientos, vegetables, olives, garlic, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Mix well and stir in consomme. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in vegetable mixture.
Pour into 8-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and garnish with tomato, lemon and cucumber slices, if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, milk, egg, sugar and corn. Pour 1/2 of mixture in iron skillet.
Sprinkle meat and 1/2 cheese on top. Add other 1/2 of cornmeal mix.
Spread rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raspberry ice
directions: Combine 2 cups cold water, fruit and lemon juice in blender container.
Cover and process on high until smooth.
Strain mixture to remove seeds.
Mix thoroughly with sugar.
Pour into ice cream canister.
Stir in remaining 1 cup of water.
Freeze as directed by ice cream freezer manufacturer.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts. You can substitute strawberries for raspberries.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with head of lettuce, in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine milk, oil and egg yolks.
Add to flour mix.
Beat smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and add to mixture.
Pour batter into waffle iron and cook.

title: boiled custard
directions: Combine milk and sugar; scald over hot water.
Beat eggs well. Add a bit of hot milk mixture; blend well.
Return to double boiler and cook over low heat until mixture coats.
Remove.
Add vanilla or nutmeg.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: wassail
directions: Bake oranges and cloves for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix cider, cinmamon and whiskey with baked oranges.
Heat and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, add and cook to boiling point first 4 ingredients.
Sift flour and sugar and add to chocolate mixture. Add last ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased cake pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix beaten eggs and sugar.
Add squash, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add and mix well. Stir in nuts and raisins or dates (optional).
Bake at 250° until done.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and dried parsley (optional).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in usual manner for corn bread.
Pour half of the mixture into greased baking pan and cover with half grated cheese.
Add remaining mixture and cover with cheese. Bake at same temperature as you would bake corn bread.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar a small amount at a time.
Add crackers and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: berline's lemon pie
directions: In the top of a double boiler, mix sugar and flour together. Add beaten egg yolks to mixture, stirring often.
Add boiling water and lemon juice or flavoring.
Continue to stir until mixture gets really thick.
Make sure the bottom of double boiler has plenty of water in it, but not enough to cause steam to rise while stirring ingredients.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: peanut butter biscuits
directions: Cut peanut butter into flour.
Add milk and mix lightly with a fork.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use milk only if icing is stiff.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg; beat well by hand, not mixer.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt, beating into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls or make small balls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Whip softened cream
cheese
and
sugar
well.	Fold in whipped cream and
add
pineapple
(well drained).	Spoon into pie shell.
Chill thoroughly about 2 hours or until filling is set. Garnish with pineapple chunks or ring.

title: monster cookies
directions: Put the oleo, white sugar and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl and cream well.
Beat in the eggs and then mix in the vanilla, white syrup and soda.
Beat in the chunky peanut butter.
Add the oatmeal and Rice Krispies and mix.
Then stir in the M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Pound to 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place a slice of ham and a slice of cheese on 1/2 of chicken breast. Fold over the other 1/2 of chicken breast.
Pinch and pound edges to seal.
Dip in flour, then egg, then crumbs. Place cutlets on wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Heat oil and butter.
Saute cutlets, turning frequently, for 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Have all boxes opened and ready to dash in before you start mixing. Roll crackers into meal effect with rolling pin.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add yeast mixture and milk to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Brush top with melted butter. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Shape as for biscuits.
Let rise (about 45 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger crunch casserole
directions: Cook meat and minced onion in shortening until meat loses it's redness. Drain off fat. Add to meat and onion mixture the mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, water and Worcestershire sauce. Pour the mixture into casserole dish and bake 5 minutes at 350°. Remove and sprinkle can of noodles on top.
Bake in oven 10 minutes longer.

title: carrot soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat for 15 minutes. Add beef broth; cook 15 minutes more.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and marjoram.
Put in blender and puree.
Serve.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Heat last 4 ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cukes and onion mixture; let stand overnight at room temperature. The next day put in containers and store in refrigerator.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve all dry ingredients in water.
Add juice.
Add water to make one gallon.
Freeze in containers to serve.
Let sit for about 4 hours.
Add ginger ale (if wanted).

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and turn on low.
Cook for 4 hours.
Before serving, add 1 cup grated cheese and allow to melt.
Could put ham in earlier if you want to.

title: ella's bean recipe
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Pour over remaining ingredients.

title: seven-layer casserole
directions: Cut up the potatoes, celery, carrots and onion in desired proportions.
Place in casserole or crock-pot in layers.
Brown ground beef and add. Cover with tomato soup and 1 can water. Place bacon on top, if desired. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered. If in crock-pot, 4 to 6 hours.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder and sugar.
Stir in eggs and oil.
Add spices and then buttermilk.
Add prunes.
Mix well. Pour in pan that is well-greased and floured.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet n sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Great served over white rice.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Add margarine and mix until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened and mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan; bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: old reliable eggnog
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat yolks well, then gradually add 1/2 cup of the sugar while still beating.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites to soft peaks, then gradually add 1/4 cup sugar while still beating.
Fold the egg mixtures together.

title: sour cream lima beans
directions: Cook beans half the time directed on the package; drain. Reserve 1/4 cup of the broth.
Place bacon in the broth.
Top with beans and cook at low heat until beans are almost tender.
Add celery, onions and salt and cook 5 minutes more.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook until hot, but do not boil.

title: ham and cheese stuffed eggplant
directions: Trim off the stem end of the eggplants.
Cut in half (lengthwise), leaving a 4-inch thick shell; scoop out and reserve the flesh.
Bring a pan of salted water to boil; add the eggplant shells.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes.
Lift out carefully with a slotted spoon and drain eggplant shells upside down.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop reserved eggplant flesh.
Melt butter in a skillet; add onion and saute for 5 minutes until soft and lightly colored.
Add the chopped eggplant; cook and stir 5 minutes. Remove from heat; mix in ham, tomato, crumbs, parsley, 1/2 of cheese and season to taste.
Mix in half broth to moisten. Arrange plant shells in single layer.
Spoon filling in shells. Sprinkle cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese has melted.

title: tomato soup(makes 8 servings)
directions: Melt margarine in large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes or until tender. Add carrots and celery.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, rice, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, thyme and hot pepper sauce.
Reduce heat to low; cook about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and let cool about 10 minutes.
In food processor or blender, process soup in small batches until smooth.
Return soup to Dutch oven; simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through. Garnish as desired.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix everything together well except the chocolate chips. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler and spread over the top.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: oatmeal bars(austin family bars)
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Melt together.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven.
Put squares of one large Hershey bar on top of warm base and spread when melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit and place in a plastic bag.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Put into bag and shake to coat. Spray Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray and place biscuits into Bundt pan.

title: cheesy spiral snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove dough from can.
Do not unroll dough.
Cut roll of dough into 8 slices; place slices on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: bread machine pumpernickel bread
directions: This bread requires double knead cycle.
Turn machine off after first knead cycle is complete.
Reset to regular bake cycle.

title: quick "stuffed" shells
directions: Mix ground beef as you would for meat loaf.
Saute in a little oil in a heavy skillet; pour off fat.
Combine sauce with ground beef; simmer until thickened.
Boil shells as directed on package (add a little oil to prevent sticking); drain.
Spread a layer of beef on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of shells. Continue; end with beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: oriental grilled cornish hens
directions: Remove giblets from hens; reserve for other uses.
Rinse hens with cold water and pat dry.
Split each hen lengthwise, using an electric knife.
Place hens, cavity side up, in a large shallow dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients; pour over hens.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix 2 cups Bisquick and water to make soft dough.
Pat into 10-inch pie pan.
Beat cottage cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine oatmeal, Bisquick, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over pie and return to oven for 10 minutes more.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and place in vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.

title: broiled fish pacifica sause
directions: Arrange fish in a single layer in shallow baking pan.
In small saucepan, combine lemon juice, butter, onion, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring until blended.
Pour sauce over fish.
Preheat broiler.
Broil fish slowly, about 4 inches from flame, basting 2 or 3 times with sauce until fish is browned and will flake when tested with fork.
Sprinkle with paprika after final basting.
The liquid keeps fish moist and tender while it broils to a golden crust.

title: easy chicken and gravy
directions: Place chicken in a large baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over chicken and bake at 350° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice or dressing.

title: chicken with gravy
directions: Cut up the fryer. Flour heavily and place in casserole or Dutch oven. Cut up the oleo or butter over chicken; cover with water. Place in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. When about half done, squeeze juice of a lemon over the chicken. Continue baking until done.

title: rustic pasta
directions: Saut onion and mushrooms in 1/4 stick of butter. Add meat to warm. Cook noodles in a large pot till they are al dente (cooked but slightly firm). Drain pasta. Melt rest of butter in large pot. Remove from heat, add noodles and toss to coat in butter. Add whipping cream, dry dressing mix and parmesan cheese. Stir until cheese is almost completely melted. Add rest of ingredients and gently toss.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Let boil; leave for 4 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/8-inch lengthwise, slicing 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt; drain in colander 30 minutes.
Press out as much moisture as possible; dry on paper towels.
Set aside.

title: mary's chicken rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except gravy, and spread on rolls.
Wrap rolls and press edges together.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Bake until golden brown.
(Can microwave for 5 to 10 minutes on High.)
Mix gravy per package directions and pour over hot rolls to serve.
Can freeze rolls.

title: ronnie's corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place mixture in greased pan. Bake in oven for 30 minutes. Take out of oven and sprinkle cheese over top of food.

title: delicious bread(for spaghetti and lasagna)
directions: Cut bread down center and spread with butter and return to foil package and heat in oven until warm.
Take out and spread the sauce on both sides of bread.
Put under broiler until brown. Slice in pieces.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir some of hot mixture into egg yolks, then immediately add to hot mixture in pan.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove and beat in butter, vanilla and marshmallows.
Put in cooked crust.
Top with meringue.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut boned chicken into large bite size pieces and place over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and sherry together.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle on cheese, then bread crumbs and drizzle melted butter over the top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 hour, until bubbly and very hot.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves at least 6.

title: mints
directions: Knead until smooth.
Roll in sugar and mold.
Food coloring is optional.

title: crowd pleasing punch
directions: In a 6 gallon container, combine water, sugar, Kool-Aid, orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and apricot nectar.
Mix well.
Just before serving, pour 1/3 punch mix into punch bowl and add 1 bottle ginger ale.
Repeat amount of punch and ginger ale as needed.
Should serve 100.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash into pieces and cook in a
small
amount
of water until
tender.
Drain
thoroughly and
mash.
Add	all remaining ingredients;
mix well and bake in	a casserole dish for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick spray.
Lay croissants flat in pan.
Sprinkle browned sausage on top.
Next, sprinkle cheese. Then pour eggs on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry beef and onion together; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, including liquid from beans and corn.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve topped with Fritos, Cheddar cheese or sour cream.

title: cabbage kraut
directions: Boil the vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, salt and sugar together. Pour over the cabbage, onion and peppers. Cool. Put in a crock or jar. Put in refrigerator or other cool place. Lasts indefinitely.

title: conch fritters
directions: Finely chop enough conch to make 1 cup.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, including conch.
Blend thoroughly.
Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil, turning once. Makes about 24 fritters.

title: easy corn on the cob
directions: Place corn with husks on, in oven directly on oven rack.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Either husk before serving or let each person do their own.

title: party punch
directions: To make sugar syrup, combine 3 cups of sugar and 3 cups of water in saucepan.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to boiling point.
Let boil without stirring about 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach pie
directions: Bake pie shell; cool.
Bring to a boil Jell-O, sugar, flour, water and oleo; let cool.
Cut fresh peaches and add to Jell-O.

title: strawberry and cream pie
directions: Mix last layer first so it can cool!

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
After mixture comes to a full boil, cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: skillet tuna patties
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, tuna, cornmeal, egg and onion. Shape into 6 patties.
In skillet, brown patties in butter. Remove. Stir remaining soup and milk into drippings. Add patties. Heat. Stir occasionally. Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired. Makes 6 servings.
M'm! M'm! good!

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Season pork chops to taste.
Layer potatoes and pork chops in crock-pot.
Pour soup on top (no need to add water).
Stir slightly.
Cook on low heat 6 to 7 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Cook and stir in milk slowly; season with salt.
Cook sauce until smooth and boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, a little at a time.
Be careful; it may curdle.
Stir constantly.
When cheese is melted, add pepper, pimento and olives.
Grease a 1-quart casserole and fill with alternate layers of potatoes and cheese sauce.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let cool before removing.

title: jane's chicken flautas
directions: Use any of the following as a dip:
sour cream (I like sour cream the best!), Pancho's hot dip, cheese dip or salad dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix egg, milk, oil and honey.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine biscuit mix, chili powder and onion powder.
Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix until moistened. Knead to form smooth dough, about 10 times on lightly floured board.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water.
Add lemon juice, rind and bag of spice after cooling syrup slightly.
Make a tea infusion (1 teaspoon tea to 1 cup freshly boiled water).
Strain and combine. Add water to make 4 quarts.

title: vegetable-beef soup with tiny dumplings(gaisburger marsch; makes 4 servings)
directions: In a heavy 6-quart flame-proof casserole or soup pot, bring the beef, bones and water to a boil over high heat, skimming off the foam and scum as they rise to the surface.
Reduce the heat to the lowest point.
Add the onion pierced with cloves, bay leaf, salt and a few grindings of pepper and simmer, partially covered, for 1 1/2 hours, skimming whenever needed.
Then remove the onion and bay leaf.
Discard and transfer the bones to a plate.
With a small spoon or the tip of a knife, scoop out the marrow from the bones.
Add it to the soup and discard the bones.
Add the celery root, carrots, parsnips, leeks and potatoes and simmer, undisturbed, for 30 minutes or until the vegetables and meat are tender.
Stir the Tiny Dumplings into the simmering soup and cook for 1 or 2 minutes longer to heat through.
Add the parsley; taste for seasoning and serve either from a large heated tureen or in individual soup bowls.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in boiler, then add your sugar, cocoa, milk and peanut butter.
When this mixture comes to a rolling boil for 3 minutes, remove from stove and add oatmeal.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Ready in minutes!

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together nuts, cheese and butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 325° until done.
Can add Rice Krispies instead of nuts if desired.

title: grandma's rugalach
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of lukewarm water.
Melt margarine and cool.
Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Combine all ingredients and form a dough.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 3 hours (don't refrigerate longer).
Divide into 8 parts.
Roll each out in sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each part into 8 triangle shapes; spread each with filling (jelly, nuts, etc.)
and roll up.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet for about 15 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine sugar, salad oil, eggs and vanilla, stirring well.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, stirring until smooth. Stir in pecans.
Add coconut, if desired, stirring well.
Spread batter evenly in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
35 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cover bottom of pan with rice.
Cover rice with 1 cup of cream of mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice and soup; then pour the second can of cream of mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups of water on top of chicken.
Sprinkle on top onion and salt to taste.
Bake in a metal pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°.
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: raspberry ring with creamy fruit
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in a bowl, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in raspberry sherbet until melted.
Pour in a 4-cup ring mold; chill until firm.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order listed in a buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine gravy, milk and pepper.
Pour over the top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine; beat in sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Blend together and pour into a deep 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brown sausage; drain. Spoon over bread. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Let sit overnight. Bake next morning in preheated 350°oven for 35 to 45 minutes. Cheese will rise to top during baking. Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until cabbage and potatoes are done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate 12 hours prior to serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients well.
Add next 3 dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal coffee cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oatmeal; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together the butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and eggs.
Add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and the oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Use a 9 x 14-inch loaf pan.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, shortening (or butter), salt, egg and 2 cups of the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)
Punch down dough.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend thoroughly with your hands. Roll into balls the size of small marbles.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until brown.

title: strawberry pudding shortcake(yields 6 servings)
directions: Combine almond milk and rice syrup in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Add grits and cook for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and mix in vanilla.
Pour into 6 individual serving dishes or one large mold.
Cover and refrigerate immediately for 2 hours to chill and prevent drying. Mix strawberries, rice syrup, lemon juice and mint.
Spoon over chilled dessert.
Garnish with mint leaves and serve.

title: cuban chicken and rice
directions: Heat water and beer; dissolve bouillon cubes in it. Separately, in 2 tablespoons oil, heat all spices and tomato sauce.
Mix spice mixture into bouillon mixture.
Place chicken pieces in mixture.
Sprinkle each with salt as you place them in mixture.
Continue to cook until chicken is tender.
When done, remove chicken from mixture and shred from bone.
Place rice in mixture and cook at low heat until rice is done.
Stir every 5 minutes.
When rice is done, add shredded chicken.
Heat a little longer as you mix the rice and chicken.
Ready to serve!
Enjoy!

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Soak peas overnight (or at least six hours) with enough water to cover peas by 2 inches; drain and rinse.
Put peas in large kettle with 6 cups hot water, bouillon cubes, white pepper and onion salt.
Bring mixture to a boil, cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until peas are just tender.
Place peas in large bowl and set aside.
Drain artichoke hearts, pouring marinade over peas.
Chop artichoke hearts to bite size pieces and toss with peas along with remaining ingredients.
Season to taste, cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken on high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer.
Transfer to warm platter.
Add onion, lime or lemon juice, brandy, parsley and mustard in pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth. Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: kirsch fruit dessert
directions: Mix fruit with grenadine syrup and Kirsch in bowl.
Cover. Refrigerate 3 hours or more.
When ready, divide mixture between 4 dessert dishes.
Top each serving with a spoon of raspberry sherbet.
Preparation time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: dutch vegetable ring
directions: Cook all together except
butter until tender or cook 3 minutes in pressure cooker (low pressure).
Arrange in ring on plate with carrots in
center.
Garnish
with
parsley or long green pickles.

title: peaches and cream
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, instant pudding, egg, margarine and milk.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Place drained peaches over batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice together and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour over top of peaches. Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. sugar mixed with 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs with milk and gradually beat in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat until smooth.
Holding the opening of a funnel closed, fill the funnel with the batter.
Open the end of the funnel to allow batter to run out in a stream into deep fat oil (375°).
Move the funnel to make a pattern, starting at the center and swirling batter outward in a circle.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until brown; turn.
Drain on paper towel when done. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 30, depending on size.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add fruit cocktail and eggs. Mix well
with spoon, do not use mixer!!!.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy salsa(kid's recipe)
directions: Cube cheese and pour salsa over.
Heat on High in microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Add all ingredients and stir just enough to moisten.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil water, chicken bouillon cubes and carrots until carrots are tender.
Then add peeled and cubed potatoes and celery.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, milk and flour to equal 1 cup.
Bring to second boil and add sour cream thickening. Rinse very well the clams.
Add, then quickly take off stove and serve.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna spinach braid
directions: For Filling:
In a large mixing bowl, combine spinach, tuna, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and garlic.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Cut peppers, onions and cucumbers into chunks.
Add vinegar and sugar; cook 15 minutes after it starts to boil.
Cut tomatoes into chunks and add to mixture.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Stir in the milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat in the oil and corn.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat (375°) until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.
Coat a 13x9 baking dish with spray.
Place eggplant slices in single layer on prepared baking sheets.
Bake for 15 minutes or until soft.
Meanwhile beat the eggs and egg whites in a shallow bowl.
Place the bread crumbs in another bowl.
Dip the eggplant slices into the egg mixture and then in the bread crumbs, pressing to coat.
Place on baking sheets.
Coat with cooking spray.
Bake the eggplant for 5 minutes or until golden.
Turn the slices. Coat with spray and bake 5 more minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°. Spread 1/3 of the Pasta sauce in the baking dish.
Top with half of the eggplant slices, half of the Mozzarella, half the Parmesan. Spread 1/3 pasta sauce over cheese layer, top with remaining eggplant slices.
Spread with
remaining pasta sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.
Diet exchange:
0 milk, 3 vegetable, 0 fruit, 1 bread, 1 1/2 meat, 1 fat.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into strips about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, meal and flour together; sprinkle over potatoes.
Top with dabs of oleo.
Cover casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Add slightly beaten eggs gradually.
Add pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate covered marshmallows
directions: Line cookie sheet with wax paper.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and yeast.
In saucepan, beat cottage cheese, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour to form a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size (45 to 65 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased (not oiled) 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: fruit squares
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients, except nuts, in
a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Put half
of mixture
in a 9 x 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Spoon
fruit filling over baked crust.
Top with crumb mixture and nuts; press lightly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.

title: cheese bennies
directions: Cream together cheese, butter, pepper and salt.
Add flour and sesame seed.
Make into a roll and wrap in wax paper; refrigerate.
Slice and bake in 350° oven until slightly golden color.

title: elephant stew
directions: After elephant is cleaned, add seasonings.
Cook in a very large pot outdoors.
Invite the entire Long Creak Baptist Church family.
Cook elephant for 4 to 5 days or until tender.
If everybody shows up, add cutup rabbit, but only as a last resort, because most people don't like "hare" in their stew.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots whole, then remove peelings.
Mix all of ingredients, except marshmallows, in blender.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
The last few minutes, add the miniature marshmallows and let melt.
Serves 10.

title: korean potato cakes
directions: Peel the potatoes.
Cut to fit the feed tube, then fit the grating disc and grate them.
Rinse and drain thoroughly, then pat them dry with absorbent paper.
In a bowl beat together the egg and the flour and season generously.
Add the grated potato and mix well.
Pour oil into a frying pan to a depth of 1/2-inch and heat.
Drop spoonfuls of the potato mixture into it and fry them, turning once or twice until the cakes are crisp and golden on both sides.

title: broccoli and rice bake
directions: Cook oleo, onion and celery about 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook for 10 minutes.
Add rice.
Add both cans of soup.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry instant pudding mix with whipped topping.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: In bowl, mix the berries with cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Top with pastry.
Prick with fork to vent.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring to boil the following:
dry mustard, oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour boiled mixture over chopped ingredients. Refrigerate at least overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: stuffing for turkey
directions: For
stuffing
a half turkey, 7 to 8 pounds, double the recipe.
For
15 pound turkey, make 4 times the recipe; for 25 pound
turkey
make
times.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add to the butter mixture alternately with milk (a little flour, a little milk).
Begin and end with flour.
Mix well after adding each ingredient.
Add flavoring and pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan; sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let cool. Add marshmallows and bananas. Chill. Cover with topping (Cool Whip).

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Cover bottom of 8 x 14-inch pan with 1/2 of mixture.

title: play dough
directions: In large pot mix all ingredients over heat.
Dough will get thick.
Keep stirring to play dough consistency.
Remove from heat and knead.
Have fun!
Do not eat!

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add other ingredients. Pour mixture into freezer container.
Freeze with a mixture of 1 part ice cream salt and 6 parts crushed ice.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together well.
Add next 6 ingredients and stir well together.
Fold in zucchini, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves (bread pan size).

title: vera hunter's 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except beans, until sugar is dissolved. Pour over beans; mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.

title: williamsburg, virginia pound cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer.
This is from the 1600's and hands were used.
In a large bowl or on tray, soften butter by kneading with hands.
Gradually work in sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add beaten egg whites and flour alternately to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings (there was no vanilla then).
Bake at 350° until done.
Can be made in small loaf pans for gifts.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil; beat until well mixed.
Add prunes and nuts; blend well. Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread thawed broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
