Heat together the soup and Cheez Whiz until smooth.
Pour over the broccoli.
Top with the fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter with a mixer. Add sugars and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Add chocolate chips and chill for 2 hours. Form into ball and roll in pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients together.
Knead. Roll into biscuits.
Makes 6 to 8 medium. Bake 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Serve hot with Grandma's molasses, butter or Welch's grape jelly. A tasty treat.

title: italian lettuce salad
directions: Mix dressing with sour cream. Place in container until serving time.

title: roast leg of lamb continental
directions: Make slits in meat with tip of sharp knife.
Insert slivers of garlic.
Rub surface of meat with salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes and onion in bottom of large, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with flour.
Place leg of lamb on top of potatoes.
Pour broth over potatoes; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain well.
Add all ingredients; put in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat all day.

title: oriental turkey stir-fry(great for leftover thanksgiving)
directions: Saute onion and garlic until clear.
Add carrot, celery and turkey; saute a few more minutes, stirring often, until turkey is browned.
Add gravy, soy sauce and ginger.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch into 1/2 cup or more of cold water.
Stir very well. Gradually add this to the turkey mixture, stirring over medium heat until bubbly and thickened.
If too thick, add water until gravy is right.
Add remaining vegetables and serve over rice or noodles.

title: microwave fruit salad
directions: Drain juice of fruits into large glass casserole to measure 3 cups liquid.
Add water if not 3 cups.
Add to this, the 2 packages of pudding.
Stir and microwave on Full power 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly and thickened.
Add fruits and stir together.
Let chill thoroughly before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Slightly mix the eggs and milk together.
Lay vegetables in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble bread on vegetables.
Pour milk and eggs over bread.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lasagna pierogi casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Pare and cook potatoes, then mash potatoes with cheese until cheese is melted.
Butter 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Layer 3 lasagna noodles, potato mixture and 1/3 onion/margarine mixture. Again layer 3 lasagna noodles, remaining potato mixture and 1/3 onion/ margarine mixture.
End with 3 lasagna noodles, remaining potato mixture and 1/3 onion/margarine mixture.
Seal pan with foil and bake 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pour over Okra and seal. Cook recommended time.

title: tasty chow chow
directions: Mix and cook 20 minutes.
One or two hot peppers can be added. Makes 11 or 12 pints.

title: chipped barbecue
directions: Cook rump roast in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.
Remove grease and chip roast with fork.
Add all ingredients and cook 1 more hour.

title: quick and easy apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and quartered apples, set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate crescent rolls.
wrap an apple quarter in each roll.
Place in an 8
inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, milk, salt and pepper; shape into 16 meatballs.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, onion, sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Turn meat occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the mushroom soup and form into patties.
Fry in nonstick pan with minimum amount of oil. Place in a baking dish and cover with mushroom soup that has been diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix cheeses and all other ingredients except pecans thoroughly.
Put in freezer until firm. Shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve with crackers.

title: corn bake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in small mixer bowl; blend in sugar and melted margarine.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to margarine mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
Cool; cut into wedges.
Serve with ice cream and hot fudge sauce.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts and place a slice of ham and cheese on each.
Roll chicken. Dip into melted margarine, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in well buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make a white sauce of flour, butter, seasoning and milk.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Add egg yolks and stir well. Let cool.
When ready to bake, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the cheese mixture.
Pour into well-buttered baking pan. Cook at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer, starting with bean dip at bottom, mixture of mayonnaise and taco dip, chopped tomatoes, chopped green pepper, sliced black olives, shredded Longhorn, Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese on top.

title: gennie's coffee cake
directions: Cream cocoa, sugar, salt and butter.
Add coffee, then buttermilk, soda and baking powder.
Add flour, then flavoring.

title: buttermilk griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and sugar onto a piece of wax paper. Combine eggs and buttermilk in a medium bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Drop batter onto a hot griddle and brown on both sides.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit with juice together.
Add bananas and apples. Sprinkle pudding mix over fruit and mix all together.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked scallops
directions: Pour 1/2 cup of the cracker crumbs in the bottom of casserole. Top with scallops.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Pour cream and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy sour cream pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Combine sour cream and soda.
Add to egg yolks.
Combine flour, baking powder and sugar.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Add butter and beat at medium speed until blended. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto hot, lightly greased skillet.
Turn when tops are bubbly and edges look cooked.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; immediately stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in the cranberries, apples, orange, and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce. Garnish with mayonnaise.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Pour prepared rhubarb juice into a large kettle; heat.
As it heats, add pectin.
Stir to dissolve.
Bring to a rolling boil. Stir in sugar; stir until it completely dissolves.
Continue to stir once in awhile.
Boil 3 minutes or until a rolling boil cannot be stirred away.
Skim.
Pour into jars and seal or seal with paraffin.

title: crock-pot easy swiss steak
directions: If you like a lot of gravy (optional), use 2 packages onion soup mix and 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water until soft; drain.
Mix sugar, egg, margarine, water, orange juice, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in apricots and nuts.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Mix 1/2 cup shredded Swiss cheese and the remaining 1/2 can onion rings.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake 10 minutes more, covered.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: I am the way, the truth and the life; no man cometh unto the Father, but by Me.

title: pour pizza
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine flour, eggs, milk, pepper and oregano, making a soft batter.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle lightly with corn meal.

title: original key west lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well. Add lime juice, blend well.
Turn into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, gradually adding sugar.
Swirl onto pie, spreading to edge of pie shell all around.
Bake in 300° oven until meringue is pale honey-colored.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in top of a double boiler over low heat.
Add noodles and nuts.
Stir lightly until all noodles are coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper (optional).
Add sauce, paste, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Add pepperoni and simmer until ready.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Stir into shredded cabbage, carrot and onions.
Let set for at least an hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While this is baking, in microwave or over low heat, melt butter and caramels with milk.
Pour on top of cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over caramel layer.
Spoon rest of batter over this.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes and then at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: zesty onion ring sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie(the easy way)
directions: Prepare pie crust as suggested on package.
While it's browning, mix milk and vanilla pudding until dissolved.
Add peanut butter and keep stirring until peanut butter is mixed well. Cook pudding, stirring constantly until very thick and almost set.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for two hours before slicing.
Can be topped with sliced bananas, whipped cream or peanut butter flavored morsels or be really bad and put chocolate peanut butter cup halves on top!

title: cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat or mix until smooth about 1 minute. Bake in greased 9 x 9 x 2 pan. Yields 9 servings.

title: sweet and sour turkey meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottom of jelly roll pans or large cookie sheets. Mix all ingredients, except sweet and sour sauce, in medium size bowl. Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls (about 20). Wet hands slightly for ease in shaping meatballs. Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer meatballs to a serving dish and drizzle with desired amount of bottled sauce.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble Oreos in large bowl.
Mix softened ice cream and Cool Whip with Oreos until well blended.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve about 1/3 of Cool Whip to spread on top.
Grate chocolate bars on top and freeze.

title: batter for fish(red snapper, amberjack, crappie)
directions: Cut fish into finger strips; salt and pepper fish to taste. Mix ingredients together with ice water until mixture is consistency of pancake mix.
Fry in deep fat.
Dip fish strips into batter, drop into fat and drain.

title: tomatoes provencale
directions: Mix together onion, parsley, garlic, butter, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges, then place into a greased, shallow, 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle tomatoes with herb mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: german green beans
directions: Reserve liquid from beans.
Cook bacon, return 2 tablespoons of fat to skillet; blend in flour and sugar.
Add vinegar and 1 cup bean liquid.
Add water,
if necessary, to make 1 cup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add onion, dill, salt and pepper.
Combine beans and potatoes in pan.
Add sauce and heat just until hot.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: worry free vegetable
directions: *(Celery, carrots, parsnips, green beans, turnip, squash, cauliflower, broccoli.)

title: tex-mex mix
directions: Layer on large skillet (seven layers):
bean dip, avocado and pepper mixture, combined yogurt, mayonnaise and taco mixture, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips surrounding the seven layered mix.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix 4 eggs, pudding mix, oil, cake mix and 7-Up.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.
When cake is finished, punch holes and pour your topping over it.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift sugar.
Add 1/2 cup butter.
Stir butter mixture into flour.
Beat in 1 egg and cream until smooth. Add raisins, nuts, applesauce and other ingredients.
Bake in greased pan 50 to 60 minutes until done.

title: wisconsin cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; saute celery, carrot and onion until tender.
Add flour and blend well.
Add chicken broth and cook until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in half and half and milk (for thicker soup, reduce half and half by 1/2 cup).
Add seasonings and bacon.
Heat, but do not boil, and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in preheated 325° oven.
Bake until mixture does not seem thin.

title: make ahead pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is of cornmeal consistency.
Beat egg; add 1 cup cold water and vinegar. Pour slowly into flour mixture, stirring with a fork until particles are moistened.
Divide pastry into 3 balls; wrap securely in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: golden angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar and baking powder together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
In a large bowl put in egg yolks and water; beat until foamy.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, beating well. Add several drops of orange flavoring and beat.
Fold in egg whites.
Put into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
If preferred drizzle with white icing glaze.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and milk.
Bake at 400° (15 to 20 minutes).
Batter may be stored in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cook potatoes
in
just
enough water to cover. Reserve water and add
tomato juice.
Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble. In	bacon
grease,	saute
onions
and green pepper. Brown beef, then
rinse and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring to 234° (soft ball stage), or until a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens on removal from water. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Add nuts.
Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread fudge in a lightly greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, gradually adding the sugar.
Mix in the oil. Measure flour, salt and baking powder; mix.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. Place on rack to cool.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in top of double boiler with generous amount of salt. Cook over boiling water until shrimp are pink.
Drain off juice.
Pack shrimp, onions, peppers and garlic juice in glass jar.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour over shrimp. Cover tightly. Be sure shrimp are completely covered with liquid.
Chill for 24 hours to 1 week, shaking jar frequently.

title: vegetarian manicotti
directions: Soak lasagna noodles in warm water for five minutes or until softened, taking care the noodles do not stick together.
Combine next 4 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese and eggs.
Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread 1 1/2 cups of vegetable mixture on bottom of pan.
Divide the Ricotta mixture equally among the softened noodles; spread evenly over each noodle. Reserve one cup of vegetable mixture; set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Add tomatoes and lettuce to top, then sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Dip with tortilla style chips.
Chill until serving time.

title: el paso burgers
directions: Grill (or fry) hamburgers to desired doneness, flattening out a little while cooking.
Drain chilies.
Place 1 or 2 chilies on burger.
Also place a few onions and top with a slice of cheese. Lower grill, cover and grill until cheese melts, or put a lid on the skillet.
Transfer to buns.
Good with mayonnaise or brown mustard.

title: quick saucy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, poultry seasoning and garlic salt in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Combine pork and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, lemon juice from concentrate, sugar, cornstarch, crushed red pepper and 1/4 cup water.
In wok or large skillet, stir-fry pork and garlic in hot oil for 3 minutes, or until brown.
Add bell pepper and onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add peanuts.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone; mix stuffing as directed on box. Spread in bottom of pan.
Cut chicken in pieces and spread on stuffing.
Dilute cream of chicken soup with chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Melt oleo and crumble crackers in oleo. Spread on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before starting, sample rum to check quality.
Good, isn't it? Now proceed.
Select large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. Check rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of proper quality, pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon of thugar and beat again.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Karo and vanilla.
Beat until mixed; add pecans and put in 2 pie crusts and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Chill in fridge, then roll into shape desired.
Bake at 400°.
Cool and decorate.

title: fresh tomato coulis(makes 2 cups)
directions: Puree 3 of the tomatoes in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl.
Dice the remaining tomato and stir it, along with the cucumber, chives and dill, into the puree. Season with salt and pepper.
Slowly stir in olive oil until incorporated.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: shells and cheese
directions: Cook noodles until done. Heat oven to 350 degrees. Place noodles in baking dish. Slice the velveeta and place on top then take the shredded cheese and sprinkle on top. Bake until all the cheese is melted.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Pour ingredients over oyster crackers and stir to coat. Place in a warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in a tight covered container.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until set.
This can be mixed together and frozen and baked later.
Allow more baking time if frozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown
ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic salt. Add other
ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, if necessary.
Serve over your favorite noodles.
Great sauce for lasagna.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix everything together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean baked lucette
directions: Alternate layers of drained beans (reserving 1/4 cup bean liquid) and onions in a baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and reserved bean liquid; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes, until heated through.
Makes six servings.

title: seafood stir-fry for two
directions: Whisk together soy sauce, sesame oil, cornstarch and clam juice.
Cut scallops in half.
Slice pepper thin.
Cut peas in half.
Chop tomato.
Heat oil and add shrimp.
Saute 30 seconds. Remove to warm dish.
Add scallops to pan and saute 20 seconds. Remove to dish with shrimp.
Add scallions, pepper, peas and tomatoes.
Return seafood to pan.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar; let stand in warm place for 15 minutes, or until bubbly. Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour.
Add flour, beating with electric mixer, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in last cup by hand.

title: cheesy ham nuggets
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Cut ham into 20 cubes.
Shape a thin layer of cheese mixture around each ham cube. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 20 servings.

title: mary's bran muffins
directions: Lightly coat with nonstick cooking spray the insides of muffin tins (1 1/2-inches deep) to accomodate about 15 muffins. Thoroughly blend together the bran, flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and raisins in a bowl.
Whisk the buttermilk, molasses, oil and egg in a bowl.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until well blended.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix first seven ingredients and form in a loaf.
Place in a shallow pan in 350° oven.
While it is starting to bake, combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Spread blueberries in crust.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla; pour over blueberries. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, then chill.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Chop apricots and mix with coconut. Add milk; mix well. Add enough sugar to allow mixture to be formed into balls. Roll in confectioners sugar. Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: This is a great recipe if you like chocolate covered cherries!

title: spanish cheese limas
directions: Cook beans in boiling water in saucepan until tender; drain. Saute celery and onions in oil in large skillet.
Add tomatoes; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in beans, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and red pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer 1/2 the bean mixture, half the cheese and remaining bean mixture in lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix flour, pecans and melted butter together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and spread on cooled crust. Mix milk, vanilla pudding and chocolate pudding together.
Spread over middle layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: french dressing
directions: In a blender, grate the onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend about 2 minutes or more.
Pour in jar and refrigerate.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Clean lettuce; drain thoroughly.
Tear into small pieces and place in large bowl.
Remove the flowerettes from the cauliflower and break into small pieces.
Arrange on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top of cauliflower.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over these ingredients and sprinkle dressing mix over the mayonnaise.
Top with frozen peas (do not need to thaw), then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover the bowl tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, toss all the ingredients together.

title: orange glazed cornish hens
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Add walnut pieces.
Place Cornish hens on individual pieces of foil; stuff with cornbread dressing.
Baste with honey (lightly).
Spoon marinade (2 to 3 tablespoons) over hens.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs together and use mixer for 4 minutes at high speed.
Stir in jam and dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into three 9-inch layer cake pans lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Mix corn, egg, milk, cheese and muffin mix.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add sour cream, salt and dill weed.
Spread onion mixture over corn mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 425°.

title: miracle whip potato salad
directions: Mix the above ingredients in a saucepan, except potatoes, and heat to boiling.
Cool slightly.
Then add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls Miracle Whip or mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Add small onion, eggs and celery to taste.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine and mix everything together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add 1 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add orange and vanilla extract.
Then add Cool Whip.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit, strawberries, bananas, grapes, pineapple or any fruit you desire.

title: clam pie
directions: Use
greased
pie
plate.
Combine
crushed
crackers, minced clams and minced onion.
Add melted butter and 1 cup of reserved liquid
from clams.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
To be used as hot spread on crackers.

title: low-fat fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, cheese, egg substitute and pimiento in a large bowl, stirring well.
Combine 1 cup milk and flour in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup milk, sugar and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to corn mixture, stirring well.
Pour corn mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole, coated with vegetable cooking spray; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add hot water to pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fat: 4.5 grams per serving.

title: low-fat cabbage
directions: Bring turkey necks to a boil; add salt and sugar to taste. Let cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, bell pepper and onion.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, including the apples.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: yakne(main dish)
directions: Brown meat and onions (season meat with seasoned salt and pepper).
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until meat is done, about 2 hours.
You may use a slow cooker.
(If so, dredge meat in 1 teaspoon flour before browning.)
Serve over rice.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips and pecans. Stir in flour.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with bottom of tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: zesty tomato chops
directions: Brown both sides of pork chops.
Add green chilies and can of tomato soup and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Thicken if needed. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil or bake hen or turkey to make broth.
Mix remaining ingredients with potato masher to break up any large chunks of bread.
Dot top with another stick margarine and sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° if using a shallow pan.
If using a deep roaster pan, bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook broccoli in salted water for about five minutes.
Drain and mix with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Place in a pie plate.
Beat mix, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour over vegetables in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown.
Let stand five minutes before cutting.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together all three ingredients.
Melt down until slow boil and completely heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy pie dough
directions: Mix all together and chill 15 minutes before rolling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Combine all ingredients and stir together in a large bowl. Spoon into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine margarine, flour, baking powder, 2 tablespoons sugar and pecans.
Press into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (about 20 minutes).
Remove from oven and cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Prepare chicken flavor rice according to package directions; chill.
Toss chilled rice with chicken, celery, raisins and onion. Combine mayonnaise with vinegar and horseradish.
Stir into chicken rice mixture.
Arrange salad on lettuce leaves and garnish with almonds.

title: chicken costa brava(mexican chicken)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt. Brown chicken in oil.
Combine spices; sprinkle over chicken.
Add garlic and onion; saute.
Add reserved pineapple juice with tomatoes, olives and salsa.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Combine milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Add flour.
Wash and cut onions into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into small balls; flatten into 1/4-inch thickness.
Top with pecans and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Make like a pie crust and work up by hand.
Press in wax paper lined 9 x 13 pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until set, but not browned.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat together 1/3 cup butter, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla in a medium bowl until fluffy.
Add egg yolk.
Mix well. Stir in flour and salt.
Press dough into twenty-four 1 3/4-inch muffin cup pan.

title: milk tart pastry
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Press into pie dish thinly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork and vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions, then brown pork cubes.
Lightly oil 12 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Arrange half the onions.
Add layer of tomatoes; salt and pepper.
Layer half of green beans, carrot and green pepper.
Top with rice.
Add pork, then rest of onions and rest of the vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add water; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Remove foil for last 30 minutes.
Check after 1 hour (add water if needed).

title: nachos supreme
directions: In a large skillet, break up ground beef.
Cook until browned.
Drain.
Pat with paper towels to remove excess fat.
Set aside.
Next spread tortilla chips to cover a large (12 inch) oven proof platter, allowing some overlap.
Arrange meat evenly over tortilla chips.
Sprinkle cheeses atop meat and chips.
Bake chips at 350 degrees for 5-7 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Spoon favorite guacamole dip over cheese and meat, followed by sour cream.
Top with olives and jalapenos.
Serve warm.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Spray 13-inch baking pan with Pam or Wesson.
Cut potatoes in bite-size chunks.
Mix with broccoli, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately one hour, turning once 1/2 way through cooking time.
After cooking, toss with cheese.
Put back in hot oven to melt and serve.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Combine soups, salsa, beans and hamburger.
Layer bean mixture, tortillas (cut up) cheese and then repeat.
Save a few tortillas and cut up to put around the edge.
Put tortillas around edge and top with cheese for the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking. Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: babka or kugel
directions: Mix altogether and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve with sour cream.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Boil chicken and save broth to make chicken soup later.
Pick meat off bones.
Slice mushrooms and onions.
Saute in butter.
Mix chicken, cream cheese, onions and mushrooms.
Stuff crescent rolls and fold up all 4 corners of roll.
Bake 17 minutes, according to package directions.

title: peanut butter cookies you won't believe
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork which has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: prime rib or roast
directions: Put roast in
pan
or
for
the
prime rib, put in meat rack. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Sprinkle some gravy mix
on
top
of
the meat and on the bottom of the pan.
Put onions on and around meat.
Add some water to bottom of pan.
Cook at 325° until done.
Add water as needed.
Makes excellent gravy.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix butter, milk and flour and pour over the other mixture and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch bread
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine bananas, sugar, eggs and melted margarine.
Add banana mixture to flour mixture alternately with milk, beating well. Stir in butterscotch chips and 2/3 cup of nuts.
Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured loaf pan; sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
This really is moist.

title: fresh mushroom stuffing
directions: Place mushrooms, onion, celery and margarine in the 3-quart microwave dish; cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in stuffing mix and enough broth to moisten (should be very moist).
Spread stuffing evenly in the dish and cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken breast glace
directions: Place first ten ingredients in heavy kettle, cover with chicken broth and cook until tender.
Allow to cool in broth.
Remove from stock and carefully skin and debone, keeping each side of breast intact.
(You now have 12 supremes.)
Cook stock down to about one pint of liquid; strain and chill.

title: cabbage-potatoes and cheese(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cut head of cabbage into bite-size pieces.
Put into large pan of water; add salt if you like.
Bring to a boil.
Peel potatoes and dice them up and add to boiling cabbage.
When the potatoes are fork-tender, drain real well.
Add Velveeta, diced and mix until cheese is melted.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and butter together.
Add flour and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cake will be like a flop with air bubbles.
